0.name: Grinning Face
0.meaning: A yellow face with simple, open eyes and a broad, open smile, showing upper teeth and tongue on some platforms. Often conveys general pleasure and good cheer or humor.

1.name: Grinning Face with Big Eyes
1.meaning: A yellow face with smiling eyes and a broad, open smile, showing upper teeth and tongue on some platforms. Often conveys general happiness and good-natured amusement.

2.name: Grinning Face with Smiling Eyes
2.meaning: A yellow face with smiling eyes and a broad, open smile, showing upper teeth and tongue on some platforms. Often conveys general happiness and good-natured amusement.

3.name: Beaming Face with Smiling Eyes
3.meaning: A yellow face with smiling eyes and full-toothed grin, as if saying Cheese! for the camera. Teeth may be smoothed-over or crosshatched. Often expresses a radiant, gratified happiness. Tone varies, including warm, silly, amused, or proud.

4.name: Grinning Squinting Face
4.meaning: A yellow face with a broad, open smile and scrunched, X-shaped eyes. Often conveys excitement or hearty laughter.

5.name: Grinning Face with Sweat
5.meaning: Has the same grin and eyes as 😄 Grinning Face With Smiling Eyes but with a single, blue bead of sweat, usually over its left eye. Intended to depict nerves or discomfort but commonly used to express a close call, as if saying Whew! and wiping sweat from the forehead.

6.name: Rolling on the Floor Laughing
6.meaning: A yellow face with a big grin and scrunched, X-shaped eyes, tilted on its side as if rolling on the floor laughing (the internet acronym ROFL). Sheds two tears and tilts right on most platforms. Often conveys hysterical laughter more intense than 😂 Face With Tears of Joy.

7.name: Face with Tears of Joy
7.meaning: A yellow face with a big grin, uplifted eyebrows, and smiling eyes, each shedding a tear from laughing so hard. Widely used to show something is funny or pleasing. Named the Oxford Dictionaries 2015 Word of the Year, and the most used emoji on all platforms from 2011-2021.

8.name: Slightly Smiling Face
8.meaning: A yellow face with simple, open eyes and a thin, closed smile. Conveys a wide range of positive, happy, and friendly sentiments. Its tone can also be patronizing, passive-aggressive, or ironic, as if saying This is fine when it’s really not.

9.name: Upside-Down Face
9.meaning: A classic smiley, turned upside down. Implemented as a flipped version of 🙂 Slightly Smiling Face on most platforms.

10.name: Winking Face
10.meaning: A yellow face with a slight smile shown winking, usually its left eye. May signal a joke, flirtation, hidden meaning, or general positivity. Tone varies, including playful, affectionate, suggestive, or ironic.

11.name: Smiling Face with Smiling Eyes
11.meaning: A yellow face with smiling eyes and a broad, closed smile turning up to rosy cheeks. Often expresses genuine happiness and warm, positive feelings.

12.name: Smiling Face with Halo
12.meaning: A yellow face with smiling eyes, closed smile, and halo, usually blue, overhead. Often represents angels, prayers, and blessings. May also convey angelic behavior, e.g., doing good deeds. See also 👼 Baby Angel.

13.name: Smiling Face with Hearts
13.meaning: A yellow face with smiling eyes, a closed smile, rosy cheeks, and several hearts floating around its head. Expresses a range of happy, affectionate feelings, especially being in love. The number of hearts (three or more) varies by platform.

14.name: Smiling Face with Heart-Eyes
14.meaning: A yellow face with an open smile, sometimes showing teeth, and red, cartoon-styled hearts for eyes. Often conveys enthusiastic feelings of love, infatuation, and adoration, e.g., I love/am in love with this person or thing.

15.name: Star-Struck
15.meaning: A yellow face with a broad, open smile, showing upper teeth on most platforms, with stars for eyes, as if seeing a beloved celebrity. Color of stars widely varies by platform, though commonly gold or red. May express that someone or something is amazing, fascinating, impressive, or exciting.

16.name: Face Blowing a Kiss
16.meaning: A yellow face winking with puckered lips blowing a kiss, depicted as a small, red heart. May represent a kiss goodbye or good night and convey feelings of love and affection more generally.

17.name: Kissing Face
17.meaning: A yellow face with simple, open eyes and puckered lips giving a kiss. Commonly conveys sentiments of love and affection.

18.name: Smiling Face
18.meaning: A classic smiley. A yellow face with a modest smile, rosy cheeks, and soft, closed eyes. Many platforms, including Apple, feature relaxed eyebrows. Conveys a wide range of warm, positive feelings, including love, happiness, and gratitude.

19.name: Kissing Face with Closed Eyes
19.meaning: A yellow face with smiling eyes, rosy cheeks, and puckered lips giving a kiss. Commonly conveys sentiments of romantic love and affection. Several platforms, including Apple, feature the same eyes and cheeks as their ☺️ Smiling Face.

20.name: Kissing Face with Smiling Eyes
20.meaning: A yellow face with smiling eyes and puckered lips giving a kiss. Commonly conveys sentiments of love and affection.

21.name: Smiling Face with Tear
21.meaning: A yellow face with open eyes, a thin closed-mouth smile, and a single tear falling from one of its eyes. Can be used to express a wide range of emotions and expressions including gratitude, tender happiness, an attempt to look happy when actually sad, or smiling through pain. Can also be a response to something that is bittersweet.

22.name: Face Savoring Food
22.meaning: A yellow face with smiling eyes and a broad, closed smile with its tongue sticking out of one corner, as if licking its lips in appetite or contentment. Widely used to convey that a food item is delicious. May also express that a person is attractive.

23.name: Face with Tongue
23.meaning: A yellow face with small, open eyes and a big grin, playfully sticking out its tongue. Can variously convey a sense of fun, excitement, silliness, cuteness, happiness, or jesting, as if saying Just kidding!

24.name: Winking Face with Tongue
24.meaning: A yellow face sticking out its tongue and making a zany wink, usually shown with its right eye closed and left wide open. Often conveys a sense of fun, excitement, wackiness, buffoonery, or joking.

25.name: Zany Face
25.meaning: A smiley making a silly face. A yellow face with a big grin and wide, white eyes, one larger than the other and in a wild, cockeyed expression. Many platforms, including Apple, depict its tongue stuck out and head tilted; others feature a full-toothed grin, giving it a more unhinged appearance.

26.name: Squinting Face with Tongue
26.meaning: A yellow face with scrunched, X-shaped eyes and a big grin, sticking out its tongue. Often conveys a sense of fun, excitement, playfulness, hilarity, and happiness, as if saying Squee! or Awesome!

27.name: Money-Mouth Face
27.meaning: A yellow face with raised eyebrows, dollar signs for eyes, and an open smile sticking out a tongue styled after a green, dollar banknote. Some platforms depict the dollar-sign eyes in green circles.

28.name: Hugging Face
28.meaning: A yellow face smiling with open hands, as if giving a hug. May be used to offer thanks and support, show love and care, or express warm, positive feelings more generally.

29.name: Face with Hand Over Mouth
29.meaning: A yellow face with a hand covering its mouth. Apple and Facebook feature simple, open eyes, suggesting someone gasping Oh my! in serious surprise, shock, concern, or apology. Other platforms depict a face with smiling eyes and/or blushing cheeks, suggesting coy laughter or embarrassment, as if cheekily saying Oops!

30.name: Shushing Face
30.meaning: A yellow face placing an index finger over pursed lips, as if issuing Shh! or Shush! for silence. Some platforms feature raised eyebrows. Apple’s design suggests the face is tilting back slightly.

31.name: Thinking Face
31.meaning: A yellow face with furrowed eyebrows looking upwards with thumb and index finger resting on its chin. Intended to show a person pondering or deep in thought. Often used to question or scorn something or someone, as if saying Hmm, I don't know about that. Tone varies, including earnest, playful, puzzled, skeptical, and mocking.

32.name: Zipper-Mouth Face
32.meaning: A yellow face with simple, open eyes and a closed zipper for a mouth. Meaning widely varies, but commonly conveys a secret or that someone will keep one (e.g., My lips are sealed). May also be used to tell someone to stop talking (e.g., Zip it! or I’ll shut up now).

33.name: Face with Raised Eyebrow
33.meaning: A yellow face with a flat, neutral mouth and furrowed eyebrows, its left raised higher than its right. Conveys a wide variety of sentiments, including suspicion, skepticism, concern, consideration, disbelief, and disapproval.

34.name: Neutral Face
34.meaning: A yellow face with simple, open eyes and a flat, closed mouth. Intended to depict a neutral sentiment but often used to convey mild irritation and concern or a deadpan sense of humor.

35.name: Expressionless Face
35.meaning: A yellow face with flat, closed eyes and mouth. May convey a sense of frustration or annoyance more intense than suggested by 😐 Neutral Face, as if taking a moment to collect itself.

36.name: Face Without Mouth
36.meaning: A yellow face with simple, open eyes and no mouth, as if at a loss for words. Meaning widely varies, but commonly conveys speechlessness, humility, and silence. May also convey moderately negative emotions, such as disappointment, frustration, or sadness.

37.name: Smirking Face
37.meaning: A yellow face with a sly, smug, mischievous, or suggestive facial expression. It features a half-smile, raised eyebrows, and eyes looking to the side. Often used to convey flirtation or sexual innuendo.

38.name: Unamused Face
38.meaning: A yellow face with slightly raised eyebrows, a frown, and eyes looking to the side. May convey a variety of negative emotions, including irritation, displeasure, grumpiness, and skepticism, as if giving the side-eye.

39.name: Face with Rolling Eyes
39.meaning: A yellow face with a small, closed mouth, flat or frowning, rolling its large, white eyes upwards. As with the gesture of an eye-roll, commonly conveys moderate disdain, disapproval, frustration, or boredom. Tone varies, including playful, sassy, resentful, and sarcastic, as if saying Yeah, whatever.

40.name: Grimacing Face
40.meaning: A yellow face with simple open eyes showing clenched teeth. May represent a range of negative or tense emotions, especially nervousness, embarrassment, or awkwardness (e.g., Eek!).

41.name: Lying Face
41.meaning: A yellow face with raised eyebrows, enlarged eyes, slight frown, and long nose, indicating it’s telling a lie in the manner of Pinocchio. Like that character, Facebook's design features a wooden nose.

42.name: Relieved Face
42.meaning: A yellow face with soft, closed eyes, raised eyebrows, and a slight smile. Facebook’s design features a slightly open mouth, as if sighing.

43.name: Pensive Face
43.meaning: A pensive, remorseful face. Saddened by life. Quietly considering where things all went wrong. Depicted as a yellow face with sad, closed eyes, furrowed eyebrows, and a slight, flat mouth.

44.name: Sleepy Face
44.meaning: A yellow face with closed eyes, mouth slightly open, and a blue snot bubble coming from its nose. Snot bubbles indicate a character is tired or sleeping in anime or manga. Not to be confused with 😴 Sleeping Face

45.name: Drooling Face
45.meaning: A yellow face, usually shown with closed eyes and raised eyebrows, with saliva drooling from one corner of its mouth. Often used to show desire for a person (sexy, attractive) or object (e.g., delicious food). May also represent someone is tired or sleeping.

46.name: Sleeping Face
46.meaning: A yellow face with eyes closed and mouth letting out three, cartoon-styled Zzz’s overhead to indicate it's sound asleep. The Zzz’s appear blue or purple across most platforms. May also represent boredom (slang, snooze).

47.name: Face with Medical Mask
47.meaning: A yellow face wearing a white surgical mask, as used by health workers in hospitals as well as the general public during a pandemic. May be worn to avoid sickness or spreading airborne diseases.

48.name: Face with Thermometer
48.meaning: A yellow face with raised or furrowed eyebrows and a thermometer in its mouth. Often depicted with red cheeks, as if feverish. May be used to represent a hospital patient or person with a cold or flu.

49.name: Face with Head-Bandage
49.meaning: A yellow face with a half-frown and white bandage wrapped around its head, often depicted partially over one eye. May represent physical injury or pain but also emotional hurting, sometimes for ironic effect.

50.name: Nauseated Face
50.meaning: A sickly-green face with concerned eyes and puffed, often red cheeks, as if holding back vomit. May represent physical illness or general disgust. Not to be confused with 🤮 Face Vomiting.

51.name: Face Vomiting
51.meaning: A yellow face with scrunched, X-shaped eyes spewing bright-green vomit. May represent physical illness or disgust, more intensely so than 🤢 Nauseated Face.

52.name: Sneezing Face
52.meaning: A yellow face with scrunched, X-shaped eyes sneezing or blowing its nose into a white tissue, as if from a cold or allergies. Often depicted with a crumpled-looking mouth.

53.name: Hot Face
53.meaning: A reddish-orange face with furrowed eyebrows, tongue stuck out, and beads of sweat, as if overheated from high temperatures. Number and position of sweat droplets vary by platforms. May also represent physical attractiveness (slang, hot).

54.name: Cold Face
54.meaning: An icy-blue face with gritted teeth usually depicted with icicles clinging to its cheeks or jaw, as if frozen from extreme cold. May also represent unfriendliness (slang, cold) or excellence (slang, cool or chill).

55.name: Woozy Face
55.meaning: A yellow face with a crumpled mouth and a cockeyed expression, as if tired and emotional from inebriation or smitten with love. Depicted with raised or furrowed eyebrows and at least one eye half-open. WhatsApp's design features a tongue hanging out.

56.name: Dizzy Face
56.meaning: A yellow face with X’s for eyes and a round, open mouth. Often depicted with raised or furrowed eyebrows. Facebook’s design features a purple forehead. Previously displayed with spiral eyes on some platforms.

57.name: Exploding Head
57.meaning: A yellow face with an open mouth, the top of its head exploding in the shape of a brain-like mushroom cloud. A visual form of the expression mind blown, it may represent such emotions as shock, awe, amazement, and disbelief.

58.name: Cowboy Hat Face
58.meaning: Yee-haw! A yellow smiley wearing a wide-brimmed, brown-leather cowboy hat. Its smile varies across platforms. May convey a sense of exuberance, whimsy, confidence, adventure, or other sentiments.

59.name: Partying Face
59.meaning: A yellow face with a party hat blowing a party horn as confetti floats around its head. Used for celebrating joyous occasions (such as New Year's Eve or World Emoji Day) and enjoying good times more generally.

60.name: Disguised Face
60.meaning: A yellow face with big glasses, a large nose, thick eyebrows, and a mustache. Used to represent someone in disguise.

61.name: Smiling Face with Sunglasses
61.meaning: A yellow face with a broad, closed smile wearing black sunglasses, as if a pair of classic Wayfarers. Often used to convey the slang sense of cool. May also express a confident, carefree attitude or that something is excellent.

62.name: Nerd Face
62.meaning: A smiling yellow face with glasses, often with teeth showing, originally buck teeth on most platforms.

63.name: Face with Monocle
63.meaning: A yellow face with furrowed eyebrows wearing a monocle. Usually depicted with a small, intent frown and head slightly upturned, as if in careful inspection.

64.name: Confused Face
64.meaning: A yellow face with open eyes and a skewed frown, as if scrunching its cheeks or chewing its lips. A look of feeling unsure. An Google’s design heightens its intended puzzlement by including contorted eyebrows.

65.name: Worried Face
65.meaning: A yellow face with open eyes, raised or furrowed eyebrows, and a broad frown. May convey a variety of moderately sad or tense emotions, including concern, anxiety, alarm, disappointment, and unhappiness.

66.name: Slightly Frowning Face
66.meaning: A yellow face with simple, open eyes and a slight frown. Often conveys a mild degree of concern, disappointment, or sadness, but usually less intensely than ☹️ Frowning Face.

67.name: Frowning Face
67.meaning: A classic sad face. A yellow face with simple, open eyes and wide, steep frown. May convey such feelings as moderate concern or disappointment and affectionate sadness, as when missing a loved one. Its sentiment is usually more intense than 🙁 Slightly Frowning Face, which has a smaller frown.

68.name: Face with Open Mouth
68.meaning: A yellow face with small, open eyes and a large, round mouth, slack with surprise or shock, as if saying Wow! or Oh my! May convey such feelings as awe or disbelief, often milder or more ironic in tone than 😱 Face Screaming in Fear.

69.name: Hushed Face
69.meaning: A yellow face with small, open eyes, raised eyebrows, and a small, open mouth, as if it has been hushed by concern or correction. Meaning widely varies, but its expression is commonly taken as surprise, embarrassment, or mild excitement.

70.name: Astonished Face
70.meaning: A yellow face with open eyes, raised eyebrows, and an open mouth, as if gasping in shock or surprise. Often depicted showing its upper teeth. May convey a wide range of emotions, including awe, amazement, admiration, disbelief, excitement, or concern.

71.name: Flushed Face
71.meaning: A yellow face with raised eyebrows, a small, closed mouth, wide, white eyes staring straight ahead, and blushing cheeks. Intended to depict such feelings as embarrassment, but meaning very widely varies. Other senses include flattery, surprise, disbelief, admiration, affection, and excitement.

72.name: Pleading Face
72.meaning: A yellow face with furrowed eyebrows, a small frown, and large, “puppy dog” eyes, as if begging or pleading. May also represent adoration or feeling touched by a loving gesture.

73.name: Frowning Face with Open Mouth
73.meaning: A yellow face with small, open eyes and an open frown. Samsung’s design shows upper teeth and tongue. Meaning widely varies, but may convey mild sadness, disappointment, concern, and amazement.

74.name: Anguished Face
74.meaning: A yellow face with small, open eyes, open frown, and raised eyebrows. Samsung’s design shows upper teeth and tongue. Meaning widely varies, but may convey alarm, confusion, or sadness, as if gasping in shock or concern.

75.name: Fearful Face
75.meaning: A face with small, open eyes, open frown, raised eyebrows, and a pale blue forehead, as if experiencing a cold flash. Samsung’s design shows upper teeth and tongue.

76.name: Anxious Face with Sweat
76.meaning: A face with open eyes and a small, open frown. Its eyebrows are furrowed, with a single bead of cold sweat dripping down, and its forehead is pale blue, as if experiencing a cold flash. Samsung's design shows upper teeth and tongue.

77.name: Sad but Relieved Face
77.meaning: A yellow face with small, open eyes, a slight frown, and furrowed eyebrows, from which a single bead of sweat drips, as if from concern or anxiety. Also known as Disappointed but Relieved Face, suggesting the smiley is upset but is grateful things didn’t turn out worse.

78.name: Crying Face
78.meaning: A yellow face with raised eyebrows and a slight frown, shedding a single, blue tear from one eye down its cheek. May convey a moderate degree of sadness or pain, usually less intensely than 😭 Loudly Crying Face.

79.name: Loudly Crying Face
79.meaning: A yellow face with an open mouth wailing and streams of heavy tears flowing from closed eyes. May convey inconsolable grief but also other intense feelings, such as uncontrollable laughter, pride or overwhelming joy.

80.name: Face Screaming in Fear
80.meaning: A yellow face screaming in fear, depicted by wide, white eyes, a long, open mouth, hands pressed on cheeks, and a pale blue forehead, as if it has lost its color. Its expression evokes Edvard Munch’s iconic painting The Scream.

81.name: Confounded Face
81.meaning: A yellow face with scrunched, X-shaped eyes and a crumpled mouth, as if quivering in frustration or holding back tears. May be used to represent being overcome with various emotions, including irritation, frustration, disgust, and sadness, as if to the point of defeat.

82.name: Persevering Face
82.meaning: A yellow face with a slight frown, furrowed eyebrows, and scrunched, X-shaped eyes, as if holding back tears or exerting great effort. May convey various degrees and tones of frustration, sadness, helplessness, and struggle. Facebook’s design features a light-purple forehead.

83.name: Disappointed Face
83.meaning: A yellow face with a frown and closed, downcast eyes, as if aching with sorrow or pain. May convey a variety of unhappy emotions, including disappointment, grief, stress, regret, and remorse.

84.name: Downcast Face with Sweat
84.meaning: A yellow face with closed eyes, frown, and a bead of sweat dripping from its forehead. Usually depicted with a single sweat bead on its right side, though Microsoft includes two.

85.name: Weary Face
85.meaning: A yellow face with closed eyes, furrowed brows, and a broad, open frown, as if distraught to the point of giving up. Usually shown with upper teeth and sometimes tongue.

86.name: Tired Face
86.meaning: A yellow face with scrunched, X-shaped eyes, furrowed eyebrows, and a broad, open frown, as if yawning in exhaustion or groaning in exasperation. Usually shown with upper teeth and sometimes tongue.

87.name: Yawning Face
87.meaning: A yellow face with eyes closed and mouth wide open covered by a hand. Captured mid-yawn, this may represent having insufficient sleep, or to imply boredom with a person or topic.

88.name: Face with Steam From Nose
88.meaning: A yellow face with closed eyes, furrowed eyebrows, broad frown, and two puffs of steam blowing out of its nose, as if in a huff or fuming.

89.name: Pouting Face
89.meaning: A red face with an angry expression: frowning mouth with eyes and eyebrows scrunched downward. Bears the same expression as 😠 Angry Face on most platforms and may convey more intense degrees of anger, e.g., hate or rage.

90.name: Angry Face
90.meaning: A yellow face with a frowning mouth and eyes and eyebrows scrunched downward in anger. Google’s design features a reddish face and Facebook’s, clenched teeth.

91.name: Face with Symbols on Mouth
91.meaning: An angry-red face with a black bar and white grawlixes covering its mouth, indicating it's swearing or being vulgar. Grawlixes are typographical symbols (e.g., @#$%&!) representing swear words or obscenities. Often used to convey an outburst of anger, frustration, or rage.

92.name: Smiling Face with Horns
92.meaning: A face, usually purple, with devil horns, a wide grin, and eyes and eyebrows scrunched downward in the same manner as 😠 Angry Face on most platforms. Google’s design is red and Facebook’s has black horns and green eyes.

93.name: Angry Face with Horns
93.meaning: A face, usually purple, with two devil horns, frowning mouth and eyes, and eyebrows scrunched downwards in anger. Bears the same expression as 😠 Angry Face and 😡 Pouting Face on most platforms. Google’s design is red and Facebook’s has black horns, green eyes, and clenched teeth.

94.name: Skull
94.meaning: A whitish-gray, cartoon-styled human skull with large, black eye sockets. Commonly expresses figurative death, e.g., dying from extreme laughter, frustration, or affection.

95.name: Skull and Crossbones
95.meaning: A cartoon human skull atop an X-shaped pair of bones, as on a pirate flag or poison symbol. Samsung’s design previously displayed a skull and crossbones on a yellow triangle, indicating a hazardous material.

96.name: Pile of Poo
96.meaning: A swirl of brown poop, shaped like soft-serve ice cream with large, excited eyes and a big, friendly smile.

97.name: Clown Face
97.meaning: A circus or birthday clown displayed with white face makeup, a red nose, exaggerated eyes and smile, and two tufts of hair (red or blue). Commonly used as comment on TikTok or other social media platforms to indicate that a person is foolish, idiotic and/or selfish.

98.name: Ogre
98.meaning: A grotesque, red face with horns, wide eyes, a large nose, crooked fangs, and a fringe of shaggy hair. Depicts an oni, a kind of hideous ogre in Japanese folklore.

99.name: Goblin
99.meaning: A menacing, red mask featuring a grotesquely long nose, angry eyes, and bushy eyebrows and mustache. Depicts a tengu, a proud trickster figure in Japanese folklore.

100.name: Ghost
100.meaning: Boo! A white, cartoon ghost making a silly face. Its tongue is stuck out and arms are outstretched, as if trying to scare someone in a friendly way. Several platforms feature one larger, bulging eye.

101.name: Alien
101.meaning: A classic alien face. The oval, bare head of a gray or green alien with large black eyes and a slight, friendly smile. Samsung depicts nostrils, Facebook a nose.

102.name: Alien Monster
102.meaning: A friendly-looking, tentacled space creature with two eyes. Most major platforms style their design after aliens in classic arcade games like Space Invaders, rendering it purple and pixellated, as if in 8-bit graphics.

103.name: Robot
103.meaning: The head of a classic robot. Commonly depicted as a vintage, tin toy robot with circular eyes, a triangular nose, knobs for ears, a light and/or antennae atop its head, and a grill-like mouth similar to a grimace. Colors vary across platform, but its head is metallic on most platforms.

104.name: Grinning Cat
104.meaning: A cartoon cat variant of 😀 Grinning Face. Depicted as yellow on major platforms.

105.name: Grinning Cat with Smiling Eyes
105.meaning: A cartoon cat variant of 😄 Grinning Face With Smiling Eyes. Depicted as yellow on major platforms.

106.name: Cat with Tears of Joy
106.meaning: A cartoon cat variant of 😂 Face With Tears of Joy. Depicted as yellow on major platforms.

107.name: Smiling Cat with Heart-Eyes
107.meaning: A cartoon cat variant of 😍 Smiling Face With Heart-Eyes. Depicted as yellow on major platforms.

108.name: Cat with Wry Smile
108.meaning: A cartoon cat variant of 😏 Smirking Face. Depicted as yellow on major platforms.

109.name: Kissing Cat
109.meaning: A cartoon cat variant of 😚 Kissing Face With Closed Eyes. Depicted as yellow on major platforms.

110.name: Weary Cat
110.meaning: A cartoon cat variant of 😩 Weary Face. Its expression more closely resembles 😱 Face Screaming in Fear. Depicted as yellow on major platforms.

111.name: Crying Cat
111.meaning: A cartoon cat variant of 😢 Crying Face. Depicted as yellow on major platforms.

112.name: Pouting Cat
112.meaning: A cartoon cat variant of 😡 Pouting Face. Also resembles 😠 Angry Face. Depicted as yellow on major platforms. Sometimes used to represent the internet meme and celebrity Grumpy Cat.

113.name: Kiss Mark
113.meaning: The mark left after a firm kiss is placed with bright lipstick. Used in place of ‘xxx’ (kisses), or to send a kiss to someone. More seductive than the kiss emoji.

114.name: Waving Hand
114.meaning: A hand waving most commonly used to say “hello” or “goodbye”.

115.name: Raised Back of Hand
115.meaning: A raised hand, showing the reverse side of the palm. May be paired with the forward-facing raised hand emoji.

116.name: Hand with Fingers Splayed
116.meaning: A raised hand with a part between each finger and the thumb. Held up in a manner that may indicate the number five. Similar to a waving hand, without any motion.

117.name: Raised Hand
117.meaning: A hand held up showing its palm. May be used to mean stop, or as a high-five.

118.name: Vulcan Salute
118.meaning: A raised hand, with the fingers separated between the ring finger and the middle finger.

119.name: OK Hand
119.meaning: A gesture showing the index finger and thumb touching to make an open circle. Represents “I’m okay” or “yes, that’s correct / good”.

120.name: Pinched Fingers
120.meaning: An emoji showing the fingers held together in a vertical orientation, often referred to as the Italian hand gesture ma che vuoi, sometimes called the "finger purse." In Italy this gesture tends to be used in disagreement, frustration, or disbelief and can mean “What do you want?” or “What are you saying?” Outside Italy anyone performing a caricature of an Italian person, regardless of context or tone, might use this gesture.

121.name: Pinching Hand
121.meaning: A hand with thumb and index finger in close proximity. Used to suggest that something is small, or to gesture a small amount. Has

122.name: Victory Hand
122.meaning: Most commonly known as a ✌️ Peace Sign, but traditionally called as a Victory Hand. Two fingers held up on one hand making a V sign.

123.name: Crossed Fingers
123.meaning: A fingers crossed emoji which displays the index (first) finger crossed over the middle (second) finger. Commonly used as a gesture indicating luck, or to show desire of a favorable outcome.

124.name: Love-You Gesture
124.meaning: The gesture for “I love you” in American Sign Language, shown as a raised pinky (little) finger, index finger, and an extended thumb.

125.name: Sign of the Horns
125.meaning: A "rock on" hand gesture raising the pinky and index fingers on one hand, which a variety of other meanings.

126.name: Call Me Hand
126.meaning: A hand with thumb and little (pinky) finger extended, making a traditional phone-like shape. May be used in conjunction with a face to suggest “call me” (please).

127.name: Backhand Index Pointing Left
127.meaning: Index finger pointing to the left.

128.name: Backhand Index Pointing Right
128.meaning: Index finger pointing to the right.

129.name: Backhand Index Pointing Up
129.meaning: Index finger pointing upward, showing the back of the hand while doing so.

130.name: Middle Finger
130.meaning: A middle finger emoji, used in some western cultures as a rude or insulting gesture. The back of the hand is shown with the middle finger raised.

132.name: Index Pointing Up
132.meaning: A single finger pointing upward, which could be used to represent the number one, or to ask a question.

135.name: Raised Fist
135.meaning: A fist raised in the air that may be used as a celebratory gesture: the fist pump. Can also be used to represent zero items, due to a lack of any fingers being held up.

136.name: Oncoming Fist

358.name: Woman Dancing
358.meaning: A person dancing, most commonly displayed as woman with one arm raised wearing a red dress, while dancing the salsa or flamenco. Often used to represent a sense of fun or as a positive affirmation, e.g. "great! 💃"

359.name: Man Dancing
359.meaning: A man dancing, added as a gender pair for the 💃 Woman Dancing. Shown on most platforms in a 70s-era suit, and one hand in the air in a disco-dancing style.

360.name: Person in Suit Levitating
360.meaning: A person wearing a suit, hovering above the ground with a shadow displayed beneath them. Generally shown wearing a fedora or similar style of hat.

361.name: People with Bunny Ears
361.meaning: An iteration of the Playboy Bunny known in Japan as a Bunny Girl. Usually depicted as an attractive woman  wearing bunny ears; a bunny girl can also be seen in anime as a hybrid human/animal known as Kemonomimi.

375.name: Kiss: Woman, Woman
375.meaning: Two women displayed kissing, or gesturing a kiss toward each other. At small sizes this may be difficult to discern from two men kissing.

406.name: Speaking Head
406.meaning: The silhouette of a person speaking. Faces left-to-right, with lines demonstrating speech being expelled. Sometimes used in the context of shouting or mansplaining.

407.name: Bust in Silhouette
407.meaning: Generic profile of one person. Often used in interface design to represent a user.

408.name: Busts in Silhouette
408.meaning: Generic profile of two people. Often used in interface design to represent users.

409.name: People Hugging
409.meaning: Two people hugging, shown as faceless blue forms on most platforms. Details of each person are not distinct and thus no options are available to customize the gender or skin tone of either individual.

410.name: Footprints
410.meaning: Two human footsteps,  showing the outline of both feet, including all five toes.

411.name: Luggage
411.meaning: A suitcase or bag, as used for traveling. Most platforms depict gray or blue rolling luggage with an extended handle. Commonly used for various content concerning traveling or taking trips, whether for business or leisure.

412.name: Closed Umbrella
412.meaning: An umbrella that is closed, likely as a result of collapsing it prior to going indoors.

413.name: Umbrella
413.meaning: An opened, dry umbrella. Generally depicted with purple fabric and a hooked handle.

414.name: Jack-O-Lantern
414.meaning: An orange pumpkin carved into the shape of a face and commonly known as a Jack-o’-lantern. See also Halloween.

415.name: Thread
415.meaning: A spool of thread, as used for sewing. Thread color varies across platforms, though often depicted in red or blue and on a wooden spool. Sometimes shown with an end unraveling.

416.name: Yarn
416.meaning: A ball of yarn, as used to knit a scarf. Color varies across platforms, but often depicted in green, blue, or magenta and shown with an end unraveling. Sometimes depicted with a pair of knitting needles stuck in the ball.

417.name: Glasses
417.meaning: Prescription glasses, shown with a variety of frames, depending on platform.

418.name: Sunglasses
418.meaning: Sunglasses that can be worn outside for protection from the sun. Often association with connotations of being "cool", or leisurely in sunny places.

419.name: Goggles
419.meaning: Clear safety goggles. When this emoji was approved in 2018 it was implied to be safety goggles rather than swimming goggles. A year later 🤿 Diving Mask, which is similar in design but used to represent swimming goggles rather than safety goggles, was approved.

420.name: Lab Coat
420.meaning: A white coat worn in a science laboratory.

421.name: Safety Vest
421.meaning: An orange safety vest with reflective lines across the chest and over the shoulders.

422.name: Necktie
422.meaning: A necktie commonly worn at work or formal occasions.

423.name: T-Shirt
423.meaning: A plain t-shirt, that can be worn by men or women. Displayed as a blue polo shirt on iOS, Facebook and Firefox OS. A white t-shirt on Android and Windows, and yellow or green on other platforms.

424.name: Jeans
424.meaning: Denim jeans, worn by men or women. A popular form of casual trousers worn by the runner emoji in Apple's emoji artwork

425.name: Scarf
425.meaning:
Scarf was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017
and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

426.name: Gloves
426.meaning:
Gloves was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017
and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

427.name: Coat
427.meaning: A winter jacket, shown in a variety of colors and styles.

428.name: Socks
428.meaning:
Socks was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017
and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

429.name: Dress
429.meaning: A pretty dress, suitable for a ball, party or other similar occasion.

430.name: Kimono
430.meaning: A traditional Japanese robe that can be worn by women or men.

431.name: Sari
431.meaning: A brightly colored sari draped in different ways across platforms. Sometimes used to mean a dress in general.

432.name: One-Piece Swimsuit
432.meaning: A sporty one-piece swimsuit shown in a variety of colors and patterns across different platforms.

433.name: Briefs
433.meaning: Underwear or swim briefs. The swimming variety are often called 'Speedos' after the brand. This emoji is shown in different colors and styles across platforms. Some platforms depict this emoji as tighty whities with a visible fly, while others use a less specific design.

434.name: Shorts
434.meaning: Shorts or swimming trunks. This emoji is shown in different colors and styles across platforms. Most platforms depict this emoji in a casual sporty style.

435.name: Bikini
435.meaning: A two-piece bikini, worn at the beach, pool, or on vacation at a tropical destination.

436.name: Woman’s Clothes
436.meaning: A blouse worn by women in a neat-casual setting.

437.name: Purse
437.meaning: A small pouch with a clasp, generally used to hold coins. Sometimes called a “coin purse.”

438.name: Handbag
438.meaning: A bag or purse, used to carry personal items, often doubling as a fashion accessory.

439.name: Clutch Bag
439.meaning: A small pouch, somewhere between the size of a handbag, and a purse.

440.name: Backpack
440.meaning: A school bag Emoji (also called a satchel) used by children attending school to carry books, lunch, and other personal belongings.

441.name: Thong Sandal
441.meaning: Flip flops, thongs or sandals, but in the singular. A single item of this casual footwear, generally worn to the beach or in warm weather.

442.name: Man’s Shoe
442.meaning: A shoe worn by a man, to work, dinner, or another occasion that requires footwear. Unlike womens shoes, this shoe is likely to be comfortable.

443.name: Running Shoe
443.meaning: A sneaker – a comfortable shoe used in sports such as tennis or golf, or for fashion purposes.

444.name: Hiking Boot
444.meaning: A style of boot commonly worn on long walks or for hiking. Generally distinct from other footwear-related emojis by the considerable grip on the sole of the shoe.

445.name: Flat Shoe
445.meaning: A flat shoe, in a style generally worn by women. More practical than a high-heeled shoe.

446.name: High-Heeled Shoe
446.meaning: A high-heeled shoe, primarily worn by women. Generally found in a context which requires formal dress, such as social occasions, or some work places.

447.name: Woman’s Sandal
447.meaning: A sandal worn by a woman in summer, spring, or other weather that suits open-toed footwear. Has a heel at the back providing additional height to the wearer.

448.name: Ballet Shoes
448.meaning: Shoes worn by ballet dancers for pointe work. Most platforms show a pair of pink shoes resting on their pointes. Sometimes used to represent dancing in general, rather than ballet specifically. Sometimes also used to represent the color pink.

449.name: Woman’s Boot
449.meaning: A tall boot generally featuring a slight heel, shown in brown or red on most platforms.

450.name: Crown
450.meaning: A gold crown with jewels on the sides. Representative of a King, Queen, or other form of Royalty.

451.name: Woman’s Hat
451.meaning: A hat worn by women for sun protection, or for fashion.

452.name: Top Hat
452.meaning: A top hat, worn in traditional British weddings and other formal occasions. This is also a popular playing piece in the game of Monopoly.

453.name: Graduation Cap
453.meaning: A graduation cap, worn on the head of students graduating from college or university. Known in some locations as a mortar board with tassel.

454.name: Billed Cap
454.meaning:
Billed Cap was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017
and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

455.name: Military Helmet
455.meaning:
Military Helmet was approved as part of Unicode 13.0 in 2020
and added to Emoji 13.0 in 2020.

456.name: Rescue Worker’s Helmet
456.meaning: A construction helmet, which is worn by the construction worker emoji in some emoji sets.

457.name: Lipstick
457.meaning: Lipstick shown with the lid removed. Displays in a shade of red on most platforms, except Android which has a pink color.

458.name: Ring
458.meaning: A ring with displaying a gem stone of some kind on the top, most likely a diamond. This piece of jewellery is often associated with a proposal and subsequent engagement to be married.

459.name: Briefcase
459.meaning: A place to store notes and other office materials. Primarily used by older people.

460.name: Drop of Blood
460.meaning: A red drop of blood. May be used to talk about bleeding, injury, blood donation, or menstruation.

461.name: Face Exhaling
461.meaning: A face showing a visible breath of air being dispelled. Used to represent relief, exhaustion, or as a sigh of disappointment or displeasure.

462.name: Face with Spiral Eyes
462.meaning: A face showing a spiral eyes, commonly used to indicate dizziness, but may also represent hypnosis or other forms of disorientation.

463.name: Face in Clouds
463.meaning: A face that appears surrounded by clouds or a haze of smoke. Ambiguous in appearance, this may represent a foggy state of mind, confusion, or even a sense of calm bliss.

464.name: See-No-Evil Monkey
464.meaning: The see no evil monkey, called Mizaru (Japanese for “see not”), one of the Three Wise Monkeys. Depicted as the brown 🐵 Monkey Face with hands covering its eyes.

465.name: Hear-No-Evil Monkey
465.meaning: The hear no evil monkey, called Kikazaru (Japanese for “hear not”), one of the Three Wise Monkeys. Depicted as the brown 🐵 Monkey Face with hands covering its ears.

466.name: Speak-No-Evil Monkey
466.meaning: The speak no evil monkey, called Iwazaru (Japanese for “say not”), one of the Three Wise Monkeys. Depicted as the brown 🐵 Monkey Face with hands covering its mouth.

467.name: Collision
467.meaning: A cartoon-styled representation of a collision. Depicted as a star-like, orange-and-yellow fiery burst, generally with one point extending to the bottom right, as if from the source of the collision.

468.name: Dizzy
468.meaning: A cartoon-styled representation of dizziness. Generally depicted as one or more yellow stars swirling in a yellow or blue circle.

469.name: Sweat Droplets
469.meaning: Three, light blue droplets, as sweat beads, splashing down to the right. Resembles plewds, stylized sweat droplets used in comics and animation to show characters working hard or feeling stressed.

470.name: Dashing Away
470.meaning: A cartoon-styled gust of air. Depicted as a small, gray cloud with motion lines, rushing to the left.

471.name: Monkey Face
471.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a monkey, looking straight ahead. Depicted as a brown-haired monkey with a tan or pinkish face, round ears, nostrils, and open-mouthed smile.

472.name: Monkey
472.meaning: A monkey, a small primate with long limbs and tail for climbing trees. Generally depicted as a cartoon-styled, brown monkey with a cheeky facial expression, shown in full profile facing left, sitting on its hind legs with a long, curled tail and round ears.

473.name: Gorilla
473.meaning: A gorilla, the powerful, black-haired great ape. Variously depicted in full profile on all fours facing left or as a friendly, cartoon-styled gorilla face looking straight ahead.

474.name: Orangutan
474.meaning: An orangutan, the orange-haired ape with long arms. Depicted facing forward, with a long broad face and sitting with its legs bent. Often shown scratching its head. Skin color varies across platforms, ranging from light to dark.

475.name: Dog Face
475.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a dog, looking straight ahead. Depicted as the face of a dog of various breeds, generally light-brown and white, with pointed or floppy ears and its tongue hanging out.

476.name: Dog
476.meaning: A dog, a faithful, beloved pet canine. Depicted as a light-brown dog, of various breeds, in full profile on all fours facing left, with a long, curled tail held upright and pointed or floppy ears.

477.name: Guide Dog
477.meaning: A guide (or Seeing Eye) dog, trained to help lead a person who is blind or visually impaired. Generally depicted as a yellowish-brown Labrador Retriever on all fours facing left, equipped with a harness and handle. Many platforms additionally include a collar.

478.name: Service Dog
478.meaning: A service animal displayed with a safety vest and lead. Differs from the guide dog as this animal is intended for detection of seizures or other “hidden disabilities”, according to the proposal from Apple.

479.name: Poodle
479.meaning: A poodle, a popular dog breed with curly hair, often groomed in an ornamental pattern.

480.name: Wolf
480.meaning: The face of a wolf, a howling canine that hunts in packs. Generally depicted as a cartoon-styled face of a gray wolf with pointed ears, white cheeks and muzzle, and black nose.

481.name: Fox
481.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled faced of a fox, the cunning canine, looking straight ahead. Depicted as an orange fox  face with a black nose, pointed ears, and shaggy, white cheeks.

482.name: Raccoon
482.meaning: A raccoon, a nocturnal mammal with a mask around its eyes. Generally depicted as a friendly, cartoon-styled, gray raccoon face looking straight ahead, with black-and-white markings around its eyes and pointed ears and cheeks.

483.name: Cat Face
483.meaning: Meow! A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a cat, looking straight ahead. Generally depicted as a yellowish-orange cat face with pointed ears and whiskers.

484.name: Cat
484.meaning: A domestic cat, beloved as a pet. Generally depicted as a light-orange cat with stripes, as a tabby, in full profile on all fours facing left, with its long tell held upright.

485.name: Black Cat
485.meaning: A black cat shown in full profile, often with its tail curling upward.

486.name: Lion
486.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a lion—the large cat and king of the jungle—looking straight ahead. Depicted as a golden-yellow lion face with a light- or dark-brown mane, white muzzle, and neutral expression.

487.name: Tiger Face
487.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a tiger looking straight ahead. Generally depicted in yellowish-orange with black stripes on its forehead and cheeks, a white muzzle, and neutral expression.

488.name: Tiger
488.meaning: A tiger, a large cat with an orange coat and black stripes. Depicted in full profile on all fours facing left, with a long tail, its distinctive stripes, and, on some platforms, white patches.

489.name: Leopard
489.meaning: A leopard, a large cat with a yellowish-brown coat and black-and-gold spots. Depicted in full profile on all fours facing left, with a long tail and its distinctive pattern.

490.name: Horse Face
490.meaning: The face of a horse, generally facing left. Depicted as a light or reddish-brown horse with a dark brown or black mane, and, on many platforms, a light-colored muzzle.

491.name: Horse
491.meaning: A horse, a hoofed mammal used for riding and racing. Depicted as a brown horse in full profile galloping to the left, with a dark, flowing mane and tail.

492.name: Unicorn
492.meaning: The face of a unicorn, a mythical creature in the form of a white horse with a single, long horn on its forehead. Generally depicted as a white horse head facing left with a pink or purple mane and a yellow or rainbow-colored horn.

493.name: Zebra
493.meaning: A zebra, a horse-like mammal with black-and-white stripes. Variously depicted in full profile on all fours facing left or as a zebra head facing left with a short mane.

494.name: Deer
494.meaning: A deer, a fleet-footed, hoofed mammal whose males (bucks, stags) generally have antlers. Variously depicted as a light-brown deer in full profile on all fours facing left or as a deer face looking straight head; both depictions feature large, branched antlers.

495.name: Bison
495.meaning: A brown bison shown in full profile with horns, a beard, and woolly mane. Also called a buffalo in North America.

496.name: Cow Face
496.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a cow looking straight ahead. Variously depicted as a white, brown, or multicolored cow face with a neutral expression, short horns, and a pink or brown muzzle.

497.name: Ox
497.meaning: An ox, a bovine used as a draft animal. Depicted in brown in full profile on all fours facing left, with a tail and short horns.

498.name: Water Buffalo
498.meaning: A water buffalo, a bovine used to plough rice fields in parts of Asia. Depicted in gray or black in full profile on all fours facing left, with a tail and broad horns curled up at the tips.

499.name: Cow
499.meaning: A cow, a bovine farmed for its meat or milk. Depicted in full profile on all fours facing left with a black-and-white patched coat (as a Holstein Friesian) and, on many platforms, a pink udder and horns.

500.name: Pig Face
500.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a pig looking straight ahead. Depicted as a pink face with a neutral expression, pointed or floppy ears, and distinctive pig nose.

501.name: Pig
501.meaning: A pig, a plump animal farmed for its meat, such as bacon. Depicted in light pink in full profile on all fours facing left, with a long snout and short, curly tail.

502.name: Boar
502.meaning: A boar, a hairy, wild pig with tusks. Generally depicted as the face of a brown boar, either facing left or looking straight ahead, with prominent tusks projecting from its lower jaw.

503.name: Pig Nose
503.meaning: The snout of a pig. Depicted as a pink oval or slightly pear-shaped nose with two black nostrils.

504.name: Ram
504.meaning: A ram, a male sheep with large, spiraling horns. Generally depicted in full profile on all fours facing left with a thick, white fleece and light-brown horns.

505.name: Ewe
505.meaning: A ewe, or female sheep raised for its wool, meat, and milk and without the spiraling horns of a ram. Depicted in full profile on all fours facing left with a thick, white fleece and black, gray, or white skin.

506.name: Goat
506.meaning: A goat, a sturdy, hoofed animal raised for its meat and milk. Depicted as a light brown, white, or multicored goat in full profile on all fours facing left, a scraggly beard, upright tail, and brown or yellow horns curving back.

507.name: Camel
507.meaning: A dromedary camel, a long-necked mammal with one large hump on its back. Depicted in light or yellowish brown in full profile on all fours facing left.

508.name: Two-Hump Camel
508.meaning: A Bactrian camel, a long-necked mammal with two large humps on its back. Depicted in light or yellowish brown, sometimes with a shaggy mane and humps, in full profile on all fours facing left.

509.name: Llama
509.meaning: A llama, a long-necked, camel-like animal, native to South America and used for transport and wool. Depicted as a shaggy white, light-brown, or multicolored llama in full profile on all fours facing left.

510.name: Giraffe
510.meaning: A giraffe, the tallest animal on Earth, with spots and a long neck. Generally depicted in yellow or tan in full profile on all fours facing left, with distinctive brown spots and small, horn-like structures.

511.name: Elephant
511.meaning: An elephant, the largest land animal on Earth, with a long trunk and, often, tusks. Generally depicted in gray in full profile on all fours facing left, with tusks and prominent ears, as an African (vs. Asian) elephant.

512.name: Mammoth
512.meaning: A brown wooly mammoth with large curved tusks. Can also be used to represent a mastodon.

513.name: Rhinoceros
513.meaning: A rhinoceros, a large mammal with one or two massive horns on its nose. Generally shown in light gray with two horns, depicted in full profile on all fours or as a rhinoceros head looking left.

514.name: Hippopotamus
514.meaning: A hippopotamus, a squat water mammal with huge jaws. Generally depicted in gray or tan in full profile facing left.

515.name: Mouse Face
515.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a mouse, looking straight ahead. Generally depicted as a gray or white mouse face with large, round ears, a pink, pointed nose, and whiskers.

516.name: Mouse
516.meaning: Eek! A mouse, a small rodent with large ears and a long tail. Generally depicted in white in full profile on all fours facing left, with pink ears, feet, and tail, often with reddish eyes.

517.name: Rat
517.meaning: A rat, a large rodent with a long tail, known to frequent big cities. Depicted in gray in full profile on all fours facing left, with pink ears, feet, and tail.

518.name: Hamster
518.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a hamster—a small rodent often kept as a pet—looking straight ahead. Generally depicted as a brown-and-white faced hamster with whiskers, a pink nose, puffy cheeks, and large, round, pink ears, sometimes with a buck tooth.

519.name: Rabbit Face
519.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a rabbit, looking straight ahead. Generally depicted as a gray and/or white rabbit face with upright ears and pink ears and nose, often with whiskers and a buck tooth.

520.name: Rabbit
520.meaning: A rabbit, a hoppy mammal with long ears. Depicted as a white, gray, or brown rabbit in full profile facing left with pink ears and a short tail, sitting on its long, hind legs or on all fours.

521.name: Chipmunk
521.meaning: A chipmunk, a small rodent with puffy cheeks. Depicted as a brown chipmunk in full profile facing left, sitting on its hind legs with a bushy tail and striped body. Generally holding an acorn or other nut in its hands.

522.name: Beaver
522.meaning: A brown beaver with buckteeth and a wide paddle-like tail. Can be used in the context of actual beavers, or metaphorically to evoke qualities of beavers like working hard, as in the expression beavering away.

523.name: Hedgehog
523.meaning: A hedgehog. A small, spiny mammal sometimes kept as a pet. Generally depicted in full profile on all fours facing left, with a round, brown body covered with spines and a light-brown face and underside.

524.name: Bat
524.meaning: A bat, the flying mammal of the night. Variously depicted as a brown, black, or gray bat, with wings outspread and pointy ears, facing forward or left.

525.name: Bear
525.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of bear, looking straight ahead. Depicted as a brown bear with round ears and a tan muzzle. Resembles a teddy bear.

526.name: Polar Bear
526.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of polar bear, looking straight ahead. Depicted as a white bear with round ears. While most platforms feature just the face of the polar bear, WhatsApp shows the full body of the bear.

527.name: Koala
527.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a koala—a bear-like marsupial known for eating eucalyptus and sleeping—looking straight ahead. Depicted as a gray face with round, fluffy ears and a large, black nose.

528.name: Panda
528.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled face of a panda—a bear-like mammal known for eating bamboo—looking straight ahead. Depicted as a white panda face with black ears and black circles around its eyes.

529.name: Sloth
529.meaning: A sloth, the slow-moving, tree-dwelling mammal. Depicted as a light-brown sloth with a wide, whitish, masked face hanging from a tree branch, facing left or right. Generally shown as a three-toed sloth.

530.name: Otter
530.meaning: An otter, the playful water mammal in the weasel family. Depicted as a light-brown otter on its back, with its forepaws held together and whiskered face to the left, generally with its long tail curled up.

531.name: Skunk
531.meaning: A skunk, a bushy-tailed mammal that sprays a foul odor when threatened. Depicted in full profile on all fours facing left, with black hair and its distinctive white stripe running from its head down to a curled-up tail.

532.name: Kangaroo
532.meaning: A kangaroo, a marsupial with a large tail and legs. Depicted in yellowish-brown in full profile facing left with large, pointed ears, shown either resting on its hind legs and tail or jumping.

533.name: Badger
533.meaning: A badger, a stocky mammal in the weasel family with a long, pointed head. Generally depicted in full profile on all fours facing left, with a gray coat, black-and-white-striped face, and short tail.

534.name: Paw Prints
534.meaning: A pair of paw prints, as left by a pet 🐈 cat or 🐕 dog. Generally depicted as two, staggered, dark-colored paw prints, each showing four toes and a pad.

535.name: Turkey
535.meaning: A turkey, a gobbling bird traditionally eaten at Thanksgiving or Christmas. Depicted in full profile facing left, standing on its legs with a dark-brown body, a white-fringed plume, pink or blue head, and its distinctive red snood and wattle.

536.name: Chicken
536.meaning: A chicken, a bird used for its meat and eggs. Generally depicted as the white head of a chicken (hen or rooster) looking left, with a yellow beak, red comb on its head, and red wattle on its neck.

537.name: Rooster
537.meaning: A rooster (cock), a male chicken known for its cock-a-doodle-do. Depicted as a white or multicolored rooster standing on its legs in full profile facing left, with a red comb on its head and red wattle on its neck.

538.name: Hatching Chick
538.meaning: A baby chicken (chick), hatching from an egg and seeing the world for the first time. Depicted as a yellow chick with an orange beak facing forward in the cracked, bottom half of a white egg, generally shown flapping its wings with a cute facial expression.

539.name: Baby Chick
539.meaning: A yellow baby chicken (chick). Variously depicted as a chick in full profile, standing on its legs, or as a chick head. Both designs show the bird facing left, with an orange beak and feet.

540.name: Front-Facing Baby Chick
540.meaning: A baby chicken (chick), shown as if flapping its wings. Depicted as a yellow chick with an orange beak in full profile standing on its legs, generally with its wings raised.

541.name: Bird
541.meaning: A generic bird. Variously depicted as a blue or red bird, as a bluebird or cardinal, shown standing in full profile, or as a bird head. Both designs show the bird facing left.

542.name: Penguin
542.meaning: A penguin, a flightless bird adapted to water and ice. Variously depicted as a full, black-bodied penguin with a white belly and orange bill or as a penguin head.

543.name: Dove
543.meaning: A dove carrying an olive branch, a symbol of peace in Western and Judeo-Christian culture. Depicted as a white bird in full profile facing left, flying as it holds a green sprig in its beak.

544.name: Eagle
544.meaning: A bald eagle, the majestic bird of prey with brown feathers and distinctive white head. Generally depicted facing left, with its wings outspread and talons out, as if swooping down to seize prey.

545.name: Duck
545.meaning: Quack! A duck, a waterbird with webbed feet. Depicted as a male (drake) mallard in full profile facing left, standing on its legs with gray and brown feathers, a yellow bill, and its distinctive green head.

546.name: Swan
546.meaning: A swan, a waterbird with white feathers and a long neck. Depicted in full profile facing left, with a curving neck, orange bill, black eye marking, and wings and legs tucked in, as if gliding in water.

547.name: Owl
547.meaning: An owl, the hooting, large-eyed bird of the night. Depicted as a reddish-brown owl, as a great horned owl, facing forward, Shown with large, round, gold-rimmed eyes, feet curled on or as if on a branch, wings tucked in, and its distinctive, horn-like tufts of feathers.

548.name: Dodo
548.meaning: A brown or gray dodo shown in full profile. Generally depicted with a curved yellow beak, small wings, a fluffy white tail, yellow or orange feet, and black talons.

549.name: Feather
549.meaning: A single feather slanted to one side. On most platforms it's light brown with a dark brown barred or striped pattern. Can be used to talk about feathers or birds, or to represent something that is lightweight, fluffy, or soft.

550.name: Flamingo
550.meaning: A flamingo, a waterbird with pink feathers and long neck and legs. Depicted as a flamingo in full profile facing left, standing on one leg, usually with a long, black beak.

551.name: Peacock
551.meaning: A peacock, the male bird that displays a large, fan-like, iridescent tale. Depicted facing forward standing on its legs, with a blue body and green tail feathers outspread.

552.name: Parrot
552.meaning: A parrot, a brightly colored tropical bird known for its ability to mimic speech. Depicted in full profile facing left standing on its legs. Variously resembles a green lovebird (with red- and-yellow-tipped wings) or a scarlet macaw (with blue-and-yellow-striped wings).

553.name: Frog
553.meaning: The face of a frog, the hopping amphibian. Generally depicted as a friendly, cartoon-styled, light-green frog looking straight ahead, with large eyes, slightly open mouth, and nostrils.

554.name: Crocodile
554.meaning: A crocodile, a stealthy reptile with massive jaws. Generally depicted as a light-green crocodile on all fours, with its long tail curving down to its toothed jaws, facing left.

555.name: Turtle
555.meaning: A turtle, a slow-moving reptile with a shell. Depicted as a light-green turtle in full profile on all fours facing left, with a long neck and green, textured shell.

556.name: Lizard
556.meaning: A lizard, a scaly reptile with a long tail. Depicted as a light-green lizard on all fours from above, generally looking left with large eyes, a lightly textured or colored back, and toes outspread, as a gecko.

557.name: Snake
557.meaning: A snake, a slithering reptile without limbs. Generally depicted as a yellowish-green snake facing left, with a long, coiled body and flicking a red, forked tongue.

558.name: Dragon Face
558.meaning: The face of a dragon, a mythical creature resembling a giant reptile found in the folklore of many cultures. Depicted as a green, Chinese-styled dragon looking straight ahead or facing left. Often shown with huge nostrils, baring large teeth and a red tongue, with antler-like structures on its head, whisker-like tendrils by its nostrils, and a green or yellow mane.

559.name: Dragon
559.meaning: A dragon, a mythical creature resembling a giant reptile found in the folklore of many cultures. Depicted as a green, Chinese-styled dragon in full profile facing left. Generally shown with a curling, snake-like body, clawed feet, yellowish scales on its back, horn-like structures on its head, and whisker-like tendrils by its nostrils.

560.name: Sauropod
560.meaning: A sauropod, a massive, plant-eating dinosaur with a long neck and tail. Depicted as a blue, gray, or green sauropod, as a brachiosaurus, apatosaurus/brontosaurus, or diplodocus. Shown in full profile on all fours facing left.

561.name: T-Rex
561.meaning: A Tyrannosaurus rex, a massive, meat-eating dinosaur with huge jaws, tiny arms, and a long tail. Depicted as a green or brown tyrannosaur standing on its hind lefts facing left, often with a textured back, sharp teeth, and clawed toes.

562.name: Spouting Whale
562.meaning: A friendly, cartoon-styled whale, shown spouting water from its blowhole. Generally depicted as a light-blue whale in full profile facing left, with a round body and white underside, its tail held upright.

563.name: Whale
563.meaning: A whale, the massive marine mammal. Generally depicted as a light-blue whale in full profile facing left, with its tail curving down towards is huge mouth. Shown with a white, textured underside, as a humpback or blue whale.

564.name: Dolphin
564.meaning: A dolphin, a sleek marine mammal known to be social and intelligent. Generally depicted as a light-blue dolphin with a white belly in full profile facing left, its short snout curving down to a prominent dorsal fin and tail, as a bottlenose dolphin leaping in the air.

565.name: Seal
565.meaning: A gray seal with dark eyes and a dark nose. Most platforms feature a design with whiskers.

566.name: Fish
566.meaning: A common fish, as swims in the water. Depicted as a generic, light-blue fish, often with a white underside, in full profile facing left, with fins and prominent gill cover.

567.name: Tropical Fish
567.meaning: A tropical fish, as swims in the warm waters of a coral reef or is kept as a pet in an aquarium. Depicted as a brightly colored fish in full profile facing left, with slender fins. Often shown as a blue-and-yellow fish with stripes, as an angelfish.

568.name: Blowfish
568.meaning: A blowfish (puffer), which puffs up and becomes spiky when alarmed. Depicted as an orange or brown blowfish in full profile facing left, with small fins, a white underside, and a round, spiky body, as if inflated.

569.name: Shark
569.meaning: A shark, a large, stealthy fish with many teeth. Generally depicted as a gray shark in full profile facing left, as a tiger, bull, or great white shark hunting in the water. Shown with a white underside and three gills, its pointed nose and teeth-lined mouth curving down to a sharp dorsal fin and long, pointed tail.

570.name: Octopus
570.meaning: An octopus, a sea animal with eight legs, known to change color and release ink. Generally depicted as a pink or orange octopus facing forward, with a large, round head, prominent eyes, and its tentacle-like arms raised at its sides. Platforms vary in the number of arms shown, ranging from four to the full eight, with several designs featuring suckers on them.

571.name: Spiral Shell
571.meaning: A seashell, as found at the beach. Generally depicted as an empty, spiraling, white seashell, as grown by a sea snail or home to a hermit crab. Positioned at various angles across platforms.

572.name: Snail
572.meaning: A snail, a slow-moving, snail-like mollusk in a spiraling shell. Generally depicted as a brown snail in full profile facing left or right, with a brown, textured shell and tentacle-like eyes.

573.name: Butterfly
573.meaning: A butterfly, a beautiful winged insect whose larva is a caterpillar. Depicted with its wings outspread, as a blue-and-black morpho butterfly or orange-and-black monarch butterfly.

574.name: Bug
574.meaning: A bug, or insect, generally depicted as a caterpillar, which becomes a 🦋 Butterfly. Shown in full profile facing left, inching up on the back of its green, segmented, and textured body. Often featuring black stripes or yellow dots and tentacles on its head.

575.name: Ant
575.meaning: An ant, a small, industrious insect that lives in a colony. Depicted as a black or red ant in full profile on its six legs facing left, with a prominent abdomen and antennae.

576.name: Honeybee
576.meaning: A honey bee, a busy, flying insect that lives in a hive and makes honey. Depicted as a black-and-yellow bee with clear or white wings and a stinger. Variously facing left in full profile or shown from above.

577.name: Beetle
577.meaning: A green or brown beetle shown with antennae and six legs. Can be used to talk about beetles, bugs, or insects in general.

578.name: Lady Beetle
578.meaning: A ladybug (ladybird, lady beetle), a beetle with a round, red shell with black spots. Generally depicted as a seven- or nine-spotted ladybug shown from above on its six legs, with antennae and its distinctively red-and-black, halved shell.

579.name: Cricket
579.meaning: A cricket, a hopping insect that makes a chirping sound. Depicted as a brown or green cricket in full profile on its six legs facing left, with long antennae and large, bent back legs.

580.name: Cockroach
580.meaning: A brown cockroach shown with antennae, six legs, and two sensory pads at its rear called cerci.

581.name: Spider
581.meaning: A spider, an eight-legged arachnid that spins a web. Depicted as a common black spider, as a house spider or funnel-web spider, shown from above with its large abdomen oriented at the bottom.

582.name: Spider Web
582.meaning: A classic spider web (cobweb), as spun by a 🕷️ Spider to catch prey. Depicted as a white, symmetrical, wheel-shaped web, as an orb web, with six or eight equal sectors.

583.name: Scorpion
583.meaning: A scorpion, an arachnid with lobster-like pincers and a stinging tail. Depicted as a light-brown scorpion from above, often facing left, with its pincers and curving stinger raised. Shown with six or, accurately, eight legs in addition to its pincers.

584.name: Mosquito
584.meaning: A mosquito, a type of bloodsucking fly. Depicted as a brown or black mosquito on its six, long legs, with wings, long abdomen, and needle-like mouth. Variously shown from above or facing left.

585.name: Fly
585.meaning: A fly with a dark or iridescent green body, six legs, and two translucent wings. On most platforms, its eyes are red.

586.name: Worm
586.meaning: A pink or brown worm. Most platforms have more realistic designs, though Google and Samsung feature cartoony worms who are smiling sweetly.

587.name: Microbe
587.meaning: A microbe, as a bacterium grown in a 🧫 Petri Dish or observed under a 🔬 Microscope. Generally depicted as a squiggly, single-celled microorganism with prominent cilia. Color, shape, and position vary across platforms. Commonly used to represent bacteria, viruses, and germs and disease more generally.

588.name: Bouquet
588.meaning: A bouquet of brightly colored flowers. Generally depicted as a collection of pink and yellow flowers with green stems tied together. Positioned at various angles across platforms.

589.name: Cherry Blossom
589.meaning: The pink flower of a cherry blossom tree. Depicted as a single, light-pink cherry blossom with five, notched petals and red-tipped stamens in a yellow or white center.

590.name: White Flower
590.meaning: A stylized white flower. Generally depicted as a rosette-shaped cherry blossom in pink or red outline, often with a white fill.

591.name: Rosette
591.meaning: A rosette, a stylized, flower-shaped decoration often presented as an award with a ribbon or (military) medal. Appears as a motif in ancient cultures. Generally depicted as a circular, yellow-and-orange flower.

592.name: Rose
592.meaning: A red rose. Depicted as a single, vertical red rose on a green stem.

593.name: Wilted Flower
593.meaning: A flower that has wilted, or is dying. Generally depicted as a limp, faded red rose drooping over the to the right on a dried-out, green stem, shedding a petal.

594.name: Hibiscus
594.meaning: A pink hibiscus, a flower that grows in warm climates. Depicted as a single, deep-pink hibiscus flower with green leaves and prominent, yellow stamen.

595.name: Sunflower
595.meaning: A sunflower, a tall, round flower with large yellow petals. Depicted as a single, vertical sunflower with a large, dark-brown center on a green stem.

596.name: Blossom
596.meaning: A flower that has blossomed. Depicted as a flower with white or yellow petals, as a daisy, with a golden center.

597.name: Tulip
597.meaning: A pink tulip flower. Depicted as a single, vertical pink tulip on a green stem.

598.name: Seedling
598.meaning: A seedling, or a young plant, as a newly sprouted tree. Depicted as a tiny, light-green plant with a short stem and two leaves. Often shown freshly sprung from a small mound of brown earth.

599.name: Potted Plant
599.meaning: A leafy green plant in pot. Plant type varies by platform.

600.name: Evergreen Tree
600.meaning: An evergreen tree, which keeps green leaves all year round. Depicted as a tall, dark green, cone-shaped tree with shaggy, layered leaves, as a pine or fir, showing a brown trunk.

601.name: Deciduous Tree
601.meaning: A deciduous tree, whose leaves change color before shedding, as 🍂 Fallen Leave, in the fall/autumn. Depicted as a generic tree with a round, lush, leafy top and brown trunk.

602.name: Palm Tree
602.meaning: A palm tree, a tree-like plant, as grows by the sea. Depicted as a palm tree with long, green, feather-like leaves and a tall, brown, segmented trunk.

603.name: Cactus
603.meaning: A cactus, a spiky plant that grows in very dry regions. Depicted as a light-green saguaro cactus with two side arms covered in spines.

604.name: Sheaf of Rice
604.meaning: A rice plant, as grown before harvesting and processing. Depicted as a sheaf of Asian rice with green leaves and yellow seed heads drooping over to the right or left. Sometimes assumed to be wheat.

605.name: Herb
605.meaning: An herb, a plant used in cooking or medicine. Depicted as a green sprig, as of basil, sage, or oregano, generally with five or seven leaves.

606.name: Shamrock
606.meaning: A shamrock, a clover-like plant. Depicted as a bright green sprig with three, heart-shaped leaves.

607.name: Four Leaf Clover
607.meaning: A four-leaf clover, a symbol of good luck. Depicted as a bright green sprig of clover, with four, heart-shaped leaves.

608.name: Maple Leaf
608.meaning: The distinctive, star-shaped leaf of the maple tree. Depicted as a reddish-orange maple leaf, as has changed color in the fall/autumn, with five pointed segments.

609.name: Fallen Leaf
609.meaning: Leaves, as a have changed color and fallen from a tree in fall/autumn. Depicted as two or three golden-brown, almond-shaped leaves of various sizes, with stems up, as if falling down.

610.name: Leaf Fluttering in Wind
610.meaning: Leaves, as fluttering in a spring or summer breeze. Depicted as one or two green, almond-shaped leaves, with gray or blue motion lines, as if swirling in the air or as the wind blowing through the trees.

611.name: Mushroom
611.meaning: The edible fungus of the mushroom, depicted as a toadstool with a white-spotted red cap and stem.

612.name: Chestnut
612.meaning: The reddish-brown, acorn-shaped chestnut, tapering to a sharp tip from its light brown base on most platforms. A popular roasted snack associated with autumn and Christmas.

613.name: Crab
613.meaning: A crab, a squat crustacean with pincers. Depicted as a reddish-orange crab (as cooked) shown from above, with a round, shelled body, shorted, tentacle-like eyes, and ten legs, the top two of which are large pincers.

614.name: Lobster
614.meaning: A lobster, a large crustacean with a prominent tail and pincers. Depicted as a reddish-orange lobster (as cooked) from above, with a long body and tail, short, tentacle-like eyes, and ten legs, the top of which are very large pincers.

615.name: Shrimp
615.meaning: A shrimp (prawn), a small crustacean with a long tail. Generally depicted as a reddish-orange shrimp (as cooked) in full profile facing left, with tiny eyes, many limbs, and its long antennae curling back as its long tail curls in.

616.name: Squid
616.meaning: A squid, an octopus-like sea animal with ten arms. Generally depicted as a pinkish-orange giant squid, facing forward or angled to the left, with a slender, arrow-like body, small eyes, and two, long arms raised up at its sides. Platforms generally depict six arms.

617.name: Globe Showing Europe-Africa
617.meaning: A globe, showing the continents of Europe and Africa in green against blue ocean.

618.name: Globe Showing Americas
618.meaning: A globe, showing the continents of North and South America in green against blue ocean.

619.name: Globe Showing Asia-Australia
619.meaning: A globe, showing the continents of Asia and Australia in green against blue ocean.

620.name: Globe with Meridians
620.meaning: A stylized globe, with blue meridians (longitudes) and latitude. Depicted with light-blue grid of lines on a white, blue, or empty circle.

621.name: Rock
621.meaning: A large rock the size of a small rock. May be considered a boulder, a rock, a stone, a pebble, or a piece of dirt. The scale and meaning are context dependent.

622.name: New Moon
622.meaning: A new moon, the first of the eight phases of the moon. Depicts the moon as a full, bluish- or grayish-black, cratered disc, not illuminated by the sun.

623.name: Waxing Crescent Moon
623.meaning: A waxing crescent moon (appearing to become larger), the second of the eight phases of the moon. Depicts the moon as a cratered disc, its right side illuminated in a thin, golden or silver crescent, its remainder dark.

624.name: First Quarter Moon
624.meaning: A first quarter moon, the third of the eight phases of the moon. Depicts the moon as a cratered disc, its right half illuminated in gold or silver, its remainder dark.

625.name: Waxing Gibbous Moon
625.meaning: A waxing gibbous moon (appearing more than half full and getting larger), the fourth of the eight phases of the moon. Depicts the moon as a cratered disc, mostly illuminated in gold or silver, but with its left side a dark crescent.

626.name: Full Moon
626.meaning: A full moon, the fifth phase of the eight phases of the moon, when it is completely lit. Depicts the moon as a full, gold or silver, cratered disc, completely illuminated by the sun.

627.name: Waning Gibbous Moon
627.meaning: A waning gibbous moon (appearing more than half full but getting smaller), the sixth of the eight phases of the moon. Depicts the moon as a cratered disc, mostly illuminated in gold or silver, but with its right side a dark crescent.

628.name: Last Quarter Moon
628.meaning: A last quarter moon, the seventh of the eight phases of the moon. Depicts the moon as a cratered disc, its left side half illuminated in gold or silver, its remainder dark.

629.name: Waning Crescent Moon
629.meaning: A waning crescent moon (appearing to become smaller), the last of the phases of the moon. Depicts the moon as a cratered disc, its left side illuminated in a thin, golden or silver crescent, its remainder dark.

630.name: Crescent Moon
630.meaning: A crescent moon, as in its waxing crescent phase. Depicts the moon as a thin, golden crescent, curving to the right and not displaying the remaining outline of the moon.

631.name: New Moon Face
631.meaning: A new moon with a smiling face, as the Man in the Moon. Generally depicts the moon as a dark disc with a slightly smiling human face and nose.

632.name: First Quarter Moon Face
632.meaning: A first quarter moon with a human face, as the Man in the Moon. Generally depicts a wide, golden crescent moon with the profile of a slightly smiling human face with a nose, facing left.

633.name: Last Quarter Moon Face
633.meaning: A last quarter moon with a human face, as the Man in the Moon. Generally depicts a wide, golden crescent moon with the profile of slightly smiling human face with a nose, facing right.

634.name: Sun
634.meaning: The sun, the star at the center of our solar system. Generally depicted as a golden-yellow disc radiating eight triangular rays, representing the sun’s heat and light.

635.name: Full Moon Face
635.meaning: A full moon with a smiling face, as the Man in the Moon. Generally depicts the moon as a dark disc with a slightly smiling human face and nose.

636.name: Sun with Face
636.meaning: A sun with a smiling face, as a Sun of May. Generally depicted as a golden-yellow disc with a smiling, often human face with a nose, radiating triangular rays, representing the sun's heat and light.

638.name: Glowing Star
638.meaning: A glowing, five-point gold star. Depicted as ⭐ Star with stylized bursts in between its points, representing glowing or twinkling.

639.name: Shooting Star
639.meaning: A stylized representation of a shooting star, a small, fast meteor that burns up in the atmosphere. Generally depicted as a gold, five-point star trailing yellow motion lines against a night sky, as if moving down to the left.

640.name: Cloud
640.meaning: A fluffy, white cloud, as a cumulus. May be used as a weather icon to represent a cloudy or overcast day.

641.name: Sun Behind Cloud
641.meaning: A yellow sun half covered by a white cloud. Position of the sun varies across platforms.

642.name: Cloud with Lightning and Rain
642.meaning: Blue raindrops falling from a white cloud with a lightning bolt flashing.

643.name: Sun Behind Small Cloud
643.meaning: A yellow sun partially covered by a small, white cloud. Position of the cloud varies across platforms.

644.name: Sun Behind Large Cloud
644.meaning: A yellow sun mostly covered by a large, white cloud. Position of the sun varies across platforms.

645.name: Sun Behind Rain Cloud
