645.meaning: A yellow sun half covered by a white rain cloud with blue raindrops. Most platforms depict the raindrops falling to the left. Position of the sun varies across platforms.

646.name: Cloud with Rain
646.meaning: A rain cloud. (Keep dry with ☔ Umbrella With Rain Drops.) Depicted as blue raindrops falling from a white cloud. Most platforms depict the raindrops falling to the left.

647.name: Cloud with Snow
647.meaning: A snow cloud. Depicted as blue snowflakes falling from a white cloud.

648.name: Cloud with Lightning
648.meaning: A thundercloud. Depicted as a yellow lightning bolt flashing from a white cloud.

649.name: Tornado
649.meaning: A tornado, a destructive column of air. Depicted as a gray, funnel-shaped cloud, rotating in contact with the ground.

650.name: Fog
650.meaning: Fog, as obscures visibility. Generally depicted as a square of a gray, hazy, cloud-like mass.

651.name: Wind Face
651.meaning: A face blowing the wind, as a personification of nature (e.g., Mother Nature, the North Wind) who creates the wind by blowing air from its mouth. Depicted as a gray, profile of a human face, generally with a feminine appearance, blowing swirls from her mouth to the right.

652.name: Rainbow
652.meaning: The colorful arc of a rainbow, as may appear after rain. Generally depicted as the left half of a full rainbow, showing six bands of color: red, orange, yellow, green, blue, and violet.

653.name: Umbrella
653.meaning: An opened, dry umbrella. Generally depicted with purple fabric and a hooked handle.

654.name: Umbrella with Rain Drops
654.meaning: An umbrella, opened to provide cover from rain. Generally depicted with purple fabric and a hooked handle with several rain droplets falling on its top.

655.name: High Voltage
655.meaning: A symbol for high voltage, as warns against injury from electricity. Depicted as a jagged yellow bolt.

656.name: Snowflake
656.meaning: The unique, feathery ice crystal of a snowflake. Depicted as a bluish-white snowflake with six intricate symmetrical branches.

657.name: Snowman
657.meaning: A classic snowman, as Frosty the Snowman, with snowflakes falling on it. Depicted as a snowman, facing forward, made from two or three large snowballs and stick arms, dressed with a top hat, a carrot nose, coal eyes, and two or three buttons on its torso. Sometimes shown with a smile and a red scarf.

658.name: Snowman Without Snow
658.meaning: A classic snowman, as Frosty the Snowman. Depicted as a snowman, facing forward, made from two or three large snowballs and stick arms, dressed with a top hat, a carrot nose, coal eyes, and two or three buttons on its torso. Sometimes shown with a smile and a red scarf.

659.name: Comet
659.meaning: A comet, an icy, rocky space object that can form a tail of gas and dust when near the sun. Generally depicted as an icy-blue comet, as if streaking downwards in a night sky.

660.name: Fire
660.meaning: A flame, as produced when something is on fire. Depicted as a red, orange, and yellow flickering flame.

661.name: Droplet
661.meaning: A single, light blue droplet, as of water, sweat, or tears.

662.name: Water Wave
662.meaning: A wave of water, as breaks at the beach. Depicted as a blue wave with a foamy, white crest, curling to the right.

663.name: Christmas Tree
663.meaning: A classic Christmas tree, an evergreen tree decorated with lights and ornaments to celebrate Christmas.  Depicted with round, variously colored ornaments and topped with a yellow star.

664.name: Sparkles
664.meaning: The glittering flashes of sparkles. Generally depicted as a cluster of three, yellow four-point stars, with one large sparkle and two small ones to its left or right.

665.name: Tanabata Tree
665.meaning: A Tanabata tree, a type of wish tree on which people hang wishes written on paper and other decorations during Tanabata, a Japanese festival celebrating two heavenly lovers. Depicted as one or two stalks of green bamboo, on which hangs one or more slips of paper, generally red.

666.name: Pine Decoration
666.meaning: A Japanese kadomatsu, composed of pine leaves and bamboo shoots. Traditionally placed outside homes in Japan around the New Year to welcome spirits for a plentiful, happy year ahead.

667.name: Grapes
667.meaning: A grape bunch, as cut from the vine and used to make wine. Depicted as red (purple-colored) grapes.

668.name: Melon
668.meaning: A melon fruit in a light greenish-brown rind. Depicted as a cantaloupe by most platforms, but can resemble a honeydew at a distance.

669.name: Watermelon
669.meaning: A slice of watermelon, showing its rich pink flesh, black seeds, and green rind.

670.name: Tangerine
670.meaning: An orange-colored citrus fruit with a green leaf or leaves and stem. Officially depicting a tangerine, a type of mandarin (mikan in Japan). Often used as a garden-variety orange. Either way, a good source of vitamin C.

671.name: Lemon
671.meaning: The sour, yellow-colored citrus fruit of the lemon, usually with a stem and green leaf or leaves.

672.name: Banana
672.meaning: A ripe banana, peeled and ready to eat on major platforms. Great snack for a child or monkey.

673.name: Pineapple
673.meaning: The tropical fruit of a pineapple, shown in spiky, golden-brown skin and with a pointed, green crown. Positioned upright or at a 45° angle.

674.name: Mango
674.meaning: The ripe fruit of a tropical mango. Variously depicted in shades of yellow, red, orange, and green with a single, green leaf and stem.

675.name: Red Apple
675.meaning: A classic red apple, shown with a stem and single, green leaf on major platforms. Commonly associated with doctors, teachers, and New York.

676.name: Green Apple
676.meaning: A common green apple, tarter counterpart to the Red Apple. Displayed with a stem and single, green leaf on major platforms.

677.name: Pear
677.meaning: A light-green variety of a common pear, shown with a stem and sometimes green leaf.

678.name: Peach
678.meaning: The fleshy, pinkish-orange fruit of the fuzzy peach, shown with green leaves and sometimes a stem.

679.name: Cherries
679.meaning: Two rich red cherries with a green leaf and joined at their long stems. May be used to refer to breasts on TikTok and other social media platforms.

680.name: Strawberry
680.meaning: The fruit of a rich red strawberry dotted with seeds and crowned with green leaves. Google previously depicted the fruit in orange.

681.name: Blueberries
681.meaning: A few ripe blueberries clustered together. Most platforms show three blueberries, and some show small green leaves coming out from behind the blueberries.

682.name: Kiwi Fruit
682.meaning: A kiwifruit, or Chinese gooseberry, with its fuzzy, brown skin sliced open to show its light-green flesh, white core, and black seeds.

683.name: Tomato
683.meaning: A plump, red garden tomato topped with a leafy green stem. May resemble the red apple at small sizes.

684.name: Olive
684.meaning: One, two, or three green olives, either pitted or sprouting from a branch. Some platforms show a solitary pitted green olive stuffed with a piece of a pimento pepper.

685.name: Coconut
685.meaning: The hairy shell of a tropical coconut, cracked in a half to show its milky-white meat. Google displays a whole coconut alongside a half-shell.

686.name: Avocado
686.meaning: A pear-shaped avocado, sliced in half to show its yellow-green flesh and large brown pit. Ready for toast, guacamole, or millennial jokes.

687.name: Eggplant
687.meaning: A long, bulbous, bright purple eggplant, or aubergine in British English, shown with a leafy stem. Considered lucky in Japan to dream of an eggplant the first night of the New Year.

688.name: Potato
688.meaning: A whole potato—such as a russet, used for baking, mashing, or frying—shown with a few eyes on its golden-brown skin. Not to be confused with the roasted sweet potato.

689.name: Carrot
689.meaning: A whole, bright orange carrot, topped with long green leaves, as if freshly plucked from the garden. Some platforms feature a longer, thinner carrot, others a shorter, more bulbous one.

690.name: Ear of Corn
690.meaning: An ear of corn, or maize, partially husked to show its buttery-yellow kernels.

691.name: Hot Pepper
691.meaning: A bright red Mexican chili pepper, slightly curled and with a green stem. May be used to represent something “hot and spicy,” figuratively or literally, as a dish on a restaurant menu.

692.name: Bell Pepper
692.meaning: A perfectly ripe red or green bell pepper. Can be used to talk about bell peppers or food in general.

693.name: Cucumber
693.meaning: A long, green cucumber with bumpy skin. Resembles its derived product, a pickle or gherkin, on many platforms, except on Apple and WhatsApp, which depict it with light-green, seed-y slices.

694.name: Leafy Green
694.meaning: A head of a rich green leaf vegetable, usually shown with white stalks. May be used to represent a variety of greens, including romaine lettuce, chard, and Chinese cabbage like bok choy, as commonly cooked in Asian cuisines.

695.name: Broccoli
695.meaning: A rich green, tree-like head or floret of broccoli.

696.name: Garlic
696.meaning: A single white or light brown bulb of garlic. Can be used to talk about cooking, eating, or vampire protection.

697.name: Onion
697.meaning: A round yellow onion. Can be used to talk about cooking, eating, or crying. Sometimes used in metaphors about layers. Might also be used in computing contexts in reference to onion routing.

698.name: Mushroom
698.meaning: The edible fungus of the mushroom, depicted as a toadstool with a white-spotted red cap and stem.

699.name: Peanuts
699.meaning: The pod of the peanut, shown in its rounded, grooved, light-brown shell. Apple depicts a pair.

700.name: Chestnut
700.meaning: The reddish-brown, acorn-shaped chestnut, tapering to a sharp tip from its light brown base on most platforms. A popular roasted snack associated with autumn and Christmas.

701.name: Bread
701.meaning: A loaf of white or wheat bread, as before it is sliced for toast or sandwiches.

702.name: Croissant
702.meaning: The flaky, golden-brown crescent of a croissant, a breakfast pastry associated with France and Austria.

703.name: Baguette Bread
703.meaning: The long, thin loaf of a baguette, with scoring on its golden-brown crust. A bread commonly associated with France.

704.name: Flatbread
704.meaning: A round piece of flatbread with grill marks. Used to represent any type of flatbread, soft or crunchy.

705.name: Pretzel
705.meaning: The heart-shaped twist of a hard or soft golden-brown pretzel, seasoned with grains of salt. A snack commonly associated with Germany.

706.name: Bagel
706.meaning: The brown bread of a bagel, shown sliced in two halves. Some platforms depict seeds, as sesame or poppy, and a schmear of cream cheese, with the bagel assembled as a sandwich. May resemble the Doughnut at small sizes.

707.name: Pancakes
707.meaning: A stack of breakfast pancakes, topped with a pad of butter and maple syrup oozing down its golden-brown sides, onto a plate on some platforms.

708.name: Waffle
708.meaning: A round or square Belgian waffle, baked to a golden brown. Most platforms depict this emoji topped with a pad of butter, and some include gooey syrup running down the sides.

709.name: Cheese Wedge
709.meaning: A wedge of yellow-orange cheese with holes, like a Swiss, but used for the food in general. May be used for various cheese-related slang expressions (e.g., “cheesy,” “say cheese,” “big cheese”).

710.name: Meat on Bone
710.meaning: A hunk of unspecified meat on a white bone, as associated with cartoon cavepersons or food in anime and manga (Japanese ano niku, “that meat”).

711.name: Poultry Leg
711.meaning: A crispy brown leg (drumstick) of chicken, duck, turkey, or other poultry on the bone, as roasted at Thanksgiving or Christmas dinner or fried at fast-food restaurants.

712.name: Cut of Meat
712.meaning: A cut of uncooked red meat, as a T-bone or rib-eye steak, with the light, white marbling of fat.

713.name: Bacon
713.meaning: Strips of crispy, fatty, reddish-brown bacon, as fried for breakfast. Depicted as a pair on most platforms.

714.name: Hamburger
714.meaning: A burger with a beef patty, usually depicted on a sesame bun with cheese, lettuce, and tomato—making it a cheeseburger, though officially called Hamburger by Unicode.

715.name: French Fries
715.meaning: Thin-cut, golden-brown French fries, served in a red carton, as at McDonald’s. Apple features Smiling Face With Smiling Eyes on its carton.

716.name: Pizza
716.meaning: A slice of pepperoni pizza, topped with black olives on Google. WhatsApp adds green pepper, Samsung white onion.

717.name: Hot Dog
717.meaning: The cooked sausage of a hot dog in a sliced bun and drizzled with yellow mustard, as eaten at a baseball game.

718.name: Sandwich
718.meaning: A sandwich, as eaten at lunch, made with lettuce, tomato, and cheese on slices of white or wheat bread. Apple, Google, and WhatsApp add a deli meat that resembles ham.

719.name: Taco
719.meaning: A Mexican or Tex-Mex taco on a hard or soft corn tortilla, filled with such ingredients as beef, lettuce, tomato, cheese, and onion. Apple’s design resembles a carne asada taco, with cilantro and white onion.

720.name: Burrito
720.meaning: A Mexican or Tex-Mex burrito, featuring a wrapped flour tortilla filled with such ingredients as beef, rice, beans, cheese, tomato, lettuce, and sour cream. Served in foil on several major platforms, suggesting a Mission burrito associated with San Francisco. Not to be confused with the Stuffed Flatbread.

721.name: Tamale
721.meaning: A single tamale wrapped in a corn husk.

722.name: Stuffed Flatbread
722.meaning: A flatbread, like pita, stuffed with lettuce, tomato, and/or meat. Resembles a doner kebab, falafel, shawarma, or gyro sandwich, popular in the Middle East and the Mediterranean. Some platforms have red onion and cucumber. Not to be confused with 🫓 Flatbread or 🌯 Burrito.

723.name: Falafel
723.meaning: Brown spheres depicting falafel, a food popular in Middle Eastern and North African cuisine, typically made of mashed chickpeas or fava beans. Most platforms include three or more falafel with one piece split open to reveal a green center. Can be used to talk about falafel and possibly other round brown food items like meatballs.

724.name: Egg
724.meaning: An egg, displayed as a chicken egg with a white or light brown shell. Commonly used at Easter time. See also: 🍳 Cooking.

725.name: Cooking
725.meaning: An egg with yolk frying in a skillet, as prepared sunny-side up. Though associated with breakfast, the emoji represents the general action of cooking and related concepts.

726.name: Shallow Pan of Food
726.meaning: A flat, shallow, black pan with side handles, containing saffron-colored rice, vegetables, a leg of poultry, and/or shrimp and lemon slices. Commonly associated with paella, a traditional dish from Spain. May be used for eating, cooking, dining, and meals more generally.

727.name: Pot of Food
727.meaning: A pot, as a casserole dish, filled with a warm and hearty beef or vegetable stew on most platforms. Generally used for eating and cooking (“a meal”), and commonly associated with soup or Japanese nabe.

728.name: Fondue
728.meaning: A red fondue pot. Most platforms show cheese fondue with fondue forks sticking out of the pot.

729.name: Bowl with Spoon
729.meaning: A bowl with a silver spoon inside, as used to eat cereal or soup. Bowl color varies across platforms, as do contents. Android depicts breakfast cereal, WhatsApp tomato soup; Apple’s is empty.

730.name: Green Salad
730.meaning: An undressed garden salad in a bowl with leafy-green lettuce and other ingredients such as tomato, red onion, and black olives. Commonly associated with healthy eating and living.

731.name: Popcorn
731.meaning: The buttery-white snack of popcorn brimming in a classic red-and-white-striped carton, as enjoyed at a movie theater.

732.name: Butter
732.meaning: A pale yellow stick of butter. Can be used to talk about cooking or eating. Might also be used in idioms or to reference something that is smooth.

733.name: Salt
733.meaning: A clear glass shaker of salt with a silver cap, as paired with pepper to season food when eating at a restaurant.

734.name: Canned Food
734.meaning: A can or tin of food, depicted as tomatoes or a generic green vegetable. May be also used to represent sauce or soup.

735.name: Bento Box
735.meaning: A Japanese bento, a lunch box divided into portions of rice, vegetables, and meat or seafood, such as sushi or fried shrimp.

736.name: Rice Cracker
736.meaning: A Japanese senbei, or rice cracker, wrapped with a sheet of nori, or seaweed, a snack commonly enjoyed with green tea.

737.name: Rice Ball
737.meaning: A Japanese onigiri, a cone-shaped ball of white rice, a snack wrapped with a sheet of nori, or seaweed.

738.name: Cooked Rice
738.meaning: A bowl of steamed white rice, a staple component of cuisine throughout Asia. Bowl color varies across platforms, though is often white.

739.name: Curry Rice
739.meaning: A plate of orange-brown curry with vegetables or meat, served with a mound of white rice. May represent kare-raisu, or Japanese curry, though commonly associated with India and other Asian cuisines.

740.name: Steaming Bowl
740.meaning: A bowl of steaming-hot food. Depicted as Japanese ramen (noodles in broth) with chopsticks on most platforms, though it can represent a warm meal more generally.

741.name: Spaghetti
741.meaning: A plate of Italian spaghetti with tomato sauce, as a bolognese, with a fork twirling its long, thin noodles. Garnished with a green herb, as parsley, on some platforms.

742.name: Roasted Sweet Potato
742.meaning: A sweet potato depicted with textured purple, orange, or brown skin and sliced in half to show its golden-brown flesh. Sometimes called a yam, though they are unrelated. Not to be confused with the Potato.

743.name: Oden
743.meaning: A skewer of three bites of Japanese oden, a winter dish made with fishcakes, tofu, konnyaku, and a variety of other ingredients, including boiled eggs. Often served as a stew or skewered and dipped into soy sauce. Resembles the Dango and may be used for other skewered foods (e.g., shish kebab, roasting marshmallows) or spears.

744.name: Sushi
744.meaning: Japanese sushi, generally depicted as two pieces of raw pinkish-orange fish, as tuna or salmon, on white rice (nigiri). Some platforms show the cylindrical maki, a piece of seafood, vegetables, and white rice wrapped in seaweed (nori).

745.name: Fried Shrimp
745.meaning: A prawn or shrimp breaded and deep-fried golden-brown. Known as ebi furai in Japan but commonly called shrimp tempura and served in a bento box. Not to be confused with the Shrimp.

746.name: Fish Cake with Swirl
746.meaning: A slice of Japanese narutomaki, a ridged fishcake of processed whitefish with an iconic pink swirl, often served in ramen or oden. Thanks to its distinct swirl, may be used for flair.

747.name: Moon Cake
747.meaning: The round, golden-brown pastry of a Chinese mooncake, a traditional delicacy and lunar symbol of the Mid-Autumn Festival. Many platforms feature a design or character imprinted on the crust, and depict a slice cut out to show a brown paste with a duck egg yolk inside. Twitter displays the Chinese character for “fall/autumn” or “harvest” (秋) on top.

748.name: Dango
748.meaning: A Japanese sweet dumpling made from rice flour and served on a skewer. Depicted as a botchan dango, comprising a pink, white or light yellow, and green ball, as colored by red beans, egg, and green tea. Resembles the Oden and featured in the Moon Viewing Ceremony, used in the Japanese festival to celebrate the full moon.

749.name: Dumpling
749.meaning: A dumpling of dough and filling, as folded and pinched closed for steaming or frying. Associated with cuisines around the world, including China (jiaozi), Japan (gyoza or dango), Poland (pierogi), and Spain and Latin America (empanada). Facebook's design resembles a xiaolongbao, a Chinese soup dumpling.

750.name: Fortune Cookie
750.meaning: A golden-brown, crescent-shaped, vanilla-flavored fortune cookie. Usually depicted with a strip of paper—on which a wise saying, lucky numbers, or Chinese vocabulary is written—peaking out of its hollow shell. Given at the end of meals at Chinese restaurants in the West.

751.name: Takeout Box
751.meaning: A tall, folded, paper carton, usually white, as used for takeout/takeaway food at Western Chinese restaurants. Most platforms depict chopsticks inside its open lid, labeled with a red, multi-tiered, traditional Chinese building. Also called an oyster pail.

752.name: Oyster
752.meaning: Half of an opened oyster shell with gray, pink, or orange flesh inside. Many platforms also include a pearl in the shell.

753.name: Soft Ice Cream
753.meaning: A swirl of soft-serve ice cream atop a wafer-style cone, white or cream-colored, as vanilla, on most platforms. Facebook’s design suggests strawberry. May be used more generally for ice cream, frozen yogurt, and frozen treats.

754.name: Shaved Ice
754.meaning: A mound of shaved ice (snow cone) served in a dessert bowl with a short spoon, flavored with a cherry-red syrup on many platforms. Associated with Hawaiian shave ice or Japanese kakigori.

755.name: Ice Cream
755.meaning: One or more scoops of ice cream in a dessert bowl, variously topped with sprinkles, wafer rolls, or cherry and syrup. Flavors vary from vanilla, chocolate, and/or strawberry across platforms.

756.name: Doughnut
756.meaning: A chocolate-glazed donut (or doughnut) with rainbow sprinkles. WhatsApp features a pink glaze associated with The Simpsons. May resemble the Bagel at small sizes.

757.name: Cookie
757.meaning: A golden-brown chocolate chip cookie or biscuit. Used to represent cookies or biscuits in general.

758.name: Birthday Cake
758.meaning: A frosted cake with lit candles, as presented for a birthday celebration. The style of cake widely varies across platforms. With white frosting and strawberries, Apple and Google’s designs suggest a Japanese Christmas cake. Other vendors depict a chocolate, pink, and/or sponge cake.

759.name: Shortcake
759.meaning: A slice of strawberry shortcake, layered with whipped cream and topped with a whole strawberry. Like the Birthday Cake, may be used to represent birthday celebrations or cake in general.

760.name: Cupcake
760.meaning: An individual cupcake in a liner topped with a swirl of frosting and sprinkles. The style of cupcake widely varies across platforms. The cake may be sponge or chocolate, the frosting pink or white, and the sprinkles rainbow or red.

761.name: Pie
761.meaning: A baked dish with a pastry crust, filled with sweet or savory ingredients. Appearance widely varies by platform. Apple depicts a whole pie in a tin, its crimped crust scored to let out steam. Google shows a slice of pumpkin pie as served at Thanksgiving, WhatsApp and Twitter a slice of cherry pie.

762.name: Chocolate Bar
762.meaning: A block of dark chocolate, usually shown in a red foil wrapper peeled back to show squares of the candy. WhatsApp displays the wrapper in purple, a color commonly associated with Cadbury chocolate.

763.name: Candy
763.meaning: A small piece of candy wrapped in plastic or wax paper with twists on its ends. Shape and color vary widely by platform. Facebook’s design used to resemble a classic unwrapped red-and-white peppermint. May also be called sweets or lollies.

764.name: Lollipop
764.meaning: A colorful lollipop made of swirled hard candy attached to a stick. Colors vary by platform, though most designs show rainbow colors or pinks and reds.

765.name: Custard
765.meaning: A golden-yellow custard dessert, as a crème caramel or flan, topped with a layer of caramel. Shown on a plate, molded in a ramekin-shape and often in a pool of caramel sauce.

766.name: Honey Pot
766.meaning: A golden-yellow pot of honey, as made by bees and desired by bears. Shown with the sweet substance oozing down its sides, often with a honey dipper inside the small vessel.

767.name: Baby Bottle
767.meaning: A bottle of milk or formula, as or fed to a baby, with a bluish cap and rubber nipple or teat. Positioned upright or at a 45° angle, and filled to various levels, sometimes showing fill lines. Often used for newborns and childrearing. See also Breast-Feeding.

768.name: Glass of Milk
768.meaning: A tall glass of white milk, as from a cow but also other mammals, nuts, or plants. Most platforms depict a glass filled near to the brim, but some show a glass half-full—or half-empty.

769.name: Hot Beverage
769.meaning: A cup of a steaming-hot beverage, usually taken as coffee or tea. Sometimes shown on a saucer. Samsung features a foamy-white tulip latte art design.

770.name: Teapot
770.meaning: A classic teapot with a wide bulbous body, a spout, a handle, and a lid. Can be used to talk about tea, tea time, or warm beverages in general.

771.name: Teacup Without Handle
771.meaning: A cup of green tea, as the minty-colored Japanese matcha, usually shown on a wooden mat. Matcha is traditionally served in a small bowl that resembles a cup without a handle. Often taken as a bowl of soup, such as a split pea.

772.name: Sake
772.meaning: Japanese sake, an alcoholic beverage made from rice. Shown as a sake set with a carafe (tokkuri) and drinking cup (choko). Most platforms show a cream colored sake set with a blue or red stripe motif. Samsung's design used to show the Japanese script for 'sake' in red along the side of the carafe.

773.name: Bottle with Popping Cork
773.meaning: A green bottle of champagne or sparkling wine with label, its cork popping to shoot out its bubbly contents. Used for a range of celebratory occasions, such as New Year's Eve, birthdays, weddings, or other life accomplishments.

774.name: Wine Glass
774.meaning: Red wine served in a stemmed glass. Google previously displayed an orange-colored drink that resembled cognac.

775.name: Cocktail Glass
775.meaning: A stemmed glass with a cone-shaped bowl, used for serving cocktails. Depicted as a martini garnished with an olive. Might be gin or vodka, shaken or stirred. See also Tropical Drink.

776.name: Tropical Drink
776.meaning: A sunset-orange-colored tropical beverage in a stemmed glass, as a rum punch or mai tai. Served with a straw and fruit garnish. Many platforms include a cocktail umbrella, hence umbrella drink. Samsung previously featured an electric-blue concoction. See also Cocktail Glass.

777.name: Beer Mug
777.meaning: A beer, as a golden-colored lager, in a frosty mug. Depicted with a frothy head spilling over the brim. Clinking Beer Mugs is a variation that displays two such beer mugs.

778.name: Clinking Beer Mugs
778.meaning: Two frosty mugs of beer with frothy heads being clinked together, as done at a celebratory or convivial toast (“Cheers!”). Several platforms include stylized lines to mark the clinking. See also Clinking Glasses.

779.name: Clinking Glasses
779.meaning: Two flutes of champagne or sparkling wine being clinked together, as done at a celebratory or convivial toast (“Cheers!”). Samsung’s design suggests two glasses of white wine. Some platforms include stylized links to mark the clinking. See also Clinking Beer Mugs—and Bottle With Popping Cork for a refill.

780.name: Tumbler Glass
780.meaning: A short, flat glass, as used for brown liquors like whiskey or Scotch whisky. Apple and WhatsApp serve theirs neat, while other platforms include ice ("on the rocks"). Samsung's glass features the faint initials ONI, an apparent in-company easter egg.

781.name: Cup with Straw
781.meaning: A drinking cup with a straw. Depicted on many platforms as a disposable cup with a lid and bendy straw, as used to serve soft drinks at fast-food restaurants. May be used for a range of non-alcoholic beverages, including milkshakes, smoothies, juice, and to-go beverages.

782.name: Bubble Tea
782.meaning: Bubble tea is a tea-based drink invented in Taiwan which typically contain tea, flavored milk, and sugar. Commonly served with tapioca pearls, also known as boba, in a plastic cup with a wide straw.

783.name: Beverage Box
783.meaning: Originally proposed as Juice, this emoji can be used to talk about juice or other liquids that come in boxes with straws. It can also be used metaphorically to talk about power, energy, respect, or an elusive quality that makes someone special.

784.name: Mate
784.meaning: Mate is a caffeinated beverage popular in many South American countries. Green in color (from a key ingredient: the dried leaves of yerba mate) and consumed via a metal straw.

785.name: Ice
785.meaning: A blue cube of ice. Can be used to talk about ice or cold temperatures in general. This emoji can also be used metaphorically to talk about something that is cool or chill.

786.name: Chopsticks
786.meaning: A pair of equal-length chopsticks, an eating utensil used throughout East Asia. Design and color vary widely by platform, though often red or wood-colored and with tips angled together. Featured in many platforms' Steaming Bowl of Food and Takeout Box. A counterpart to utensils such as Fork and Knife and Spoon.

787.name: Fork and Knife with Plate
787.meaning: A silver fork and knife on either side of a white plate, as set for dinner or another meal. Often used more generally for eating and dining. May be paired with Spoon.

788.name: Fork and Knife
788.meaning: A silver fork to the left of a knife, silverware or cutlery used to eat a meal. Often used more generally for eating and dining. May be paired with Spoon or used with Fork and Knife With Plate.

789.name: Spoon
789.meaning: A silver spoon, as used to eat soup, cereal, or ice cream as well as serve food or stir drinks. Positioned at various angles across platforms. May be paired with Fork and Knife, Fork and Knife With Plate, and Bowl With Spoon.

790.name: Person in Suit Levitating
790.meaning: A person wearing a suit, hovering above the ground with a shadow displayed beneath them. Generally shown wearing a fedora or similar style of hat.

791.name: Person Climbing
791.meaning: A rock climber, shown climbing up a rock formation. Some platforms show the climber with a helmet and/or rope. The Emojipedia Sample image was created with assistance from World Champion Rock Climber Sasha DiGiulian.

792.name: Man Climbing
792.meaning: A male rock climber, shown climbing up a rock formation. Some platforms show the climber with a helmet, and/or rope.

793.name: Woman Climbing
793.meaning: A female rock climber, shown climbing up a rock formation. Some platforms show the climber with a helmet, and/or rope.

794.name: Person Fencing
794.meaning: A person shown in the sport of fencing, with a Rapier-style sword, mask, and protective clothing.

795.name: Horse Racing
795.meaning: A jockey riding a horse in a horse race. Shown riding to the left of screen on all major platforms. Emoji modifiers change the skin tone of the jockey on some platforms, which can be difficult to discern at small sizes.

796.name: Skier
796.meaning: A person downhill-skiiing. Displayed with poles and skis, generally wearing a mask.

797.name: Snowboarder
797.meaning: A person snowboarding downhill at a ski resort. Wearing clothing designed for cold climates.

798.name: Person Golfing
798.meaning: A person swinging a golf club, attempting to hit a golf ball toward the flag on the green.

799.name: Man Golfing
799.meaning: The male version of the 🏌 Golfer emoji. Currently identical in appearance to the non-gendered base emoji.

800.name: Woman Golfing
800.meaning: The female version of the 🏌 Golfer emoji.

801.name: Person Surfing
801.meaning: A person on a surfboard, riding on a wave in the ocean. Wears a wetsuit or board shorts in most versions.

802.name: Man Surfing
802.meaning: The male version of the 🏄 Surfer emoji. Currently identical in appearance to the non-gendered base emoji.

803.name: Woman Surfing
803.meaning: The female version of the 🏄 Surfer emoji.

804.name: Person Rowing Boat
804.meaning: A small rowboat suitable for a small number of people. Couples or families sometimes hire these as an activity on calm waters.

805.name: Man Rowing Boat
805.meaning: The male version of the 🚣 Rowboat emoji. Currently identical in appearance to the non-gendered base emoji.

806.name: Woman Rowing Boat
806.meaning: The female version of the 🚣 Rowboat emoji.

807.name: Person Swimming
807.meaning: A person swimming in a pool, the ocean, or another body of water. Lacked goggles on prior versions of iOS.

808.name: Man Swimming
808.meaning: The male version of the 🏊 Swimmer emoji. Currently identical in appearance to the non-gendered base emoji.

809.name: Woman Swimming
809.meaning: The female version of the 🏊 Swimmer emoji.

810.name: Person Bouncing Ball
810.meaning: A person with a ball, which is generally displayed as a basketballer running and dribbling (bouncing) the basketball.

811.name: Man Bouncing Ball
811.meaning: The male version of the ⛹ Person With Ball emoji. Currently identical in appearance to the non-gendered base emoji.

812.name: Woman Bouncing Ball
812.meaning: The female version of the ⛹ Person With Ball emoji.

813.name: Person Lifting Weights
813.meaning: A person lifting a barbell loaded with weights above their head.

814.name: Man Lifting Weights
814.meaning: The male version of the 🏋 Weight Lifter emoji. Currently identical in appearance to the non-gendered base emoji.

815.name: Woman Lifting Weights
815.meaning: The female version of the 🏋 Weight Lifter emoji.

816.name: Person Biking
816.meaning: A person riding a bicycle for leisure, sport or transport. Intended to be gender-neutral.

817.name: Man Biking
817.meaning: The male version of the 🚴 Bicyclist emoji. Currently identical in appearance to the non-gendered base emoji.

818.name: Woman Biking
818.meaning: The female version of the 🚴 Bicyclist emoji.

819.name: Person Mountain Biking
819.meaning: A person (cyclist) who rides a mountain bike: a type of off-road bicycle. Intended to be gender-neutral.

820.name: Man Mountain Biking
820.meaning: The male version of the 🚵 Mountain Bicyclist emoji. Currently identical in appearance to the non-gendered base emoji.

821.name: Woman Mountain Biking
821.meaning: The female version of the 🚵 Mountain Bicyclist emoji.

822.name: Person Cartwheeling
822.meaning: A person doing a cartwheel, representing the sport of gymnastics.

823.name: Man Cartwheeling
823.meaning:
The Man Cartwheeling emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤸 Person Cartwheeling, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♂️ Male Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

824.name: Woman Cartwheeling
824.meaning:
The Woman Cartwheeling emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤸 Person Cartwheeling, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♀️ Female Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

825.name: People Wrestling
825.meaning: Two people in the sport of wrestling.

826.name: Men Wrestling
826.meaning:
The Men Wrestling emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤼 People Wrestling, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♂️ Male Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

827.name: Women Wrestling
827.meaning:
The Women Wrestling emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤼 People Wrestling, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♀️ Female Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

828.name: Person Playing Water Polo
828.meaning: A person shown in water with a ball, playing the sport of water polo.

829.name: Man Playing Water Polo
829.meaning:
The Man Playing Water Polo emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤽 Person Playing Water Polo, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♂️ Male Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

830.name: Woman Playing Water Polo
830.meaning:
The Woman Playing Water Polo emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤽 Person Playing Water Polo, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♀️ Female Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

831.name: Person Playing Handball
831.meaning:
Person Playing Handball was approved as part of Unicode 9.0 in 2016
under the name “Handball”
and added to Emoji 3.0 in 2016.

832.name: Man Playing Handball
832.meaning:
The Man Playing Handball emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤾 Person Playing Handball, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♂️ Male Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

833.name: Woman Playing Handball
833.meaning:
The Woman Playing Handball emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤾 Person Playing Handball, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♀️ Female Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

834.name: Person Juggling
834.meaning: A person juggling between three and five colored balls. The person shown in this emoji generally has the appearance of a man, and wears a hat on most major platforms.

835.name: Man Juggling
835.meaning:
The Man Juggling emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤹 Person Juggling, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♂️ Male Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

836.name: Woman Juggling
836.meaning:
The Woman Juggling emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🤹 Person Juggling, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♀️ Female Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

837.name: Person in Lotus Position
837.meaning:
Person in Lotus Position was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017
and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

838.name: Man in Lotus Position
838.meaning:
The Man in Lotus Position emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🧘 Person in Lotus Position, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♂️ Male Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

839.name: Woman in Lotus Position
839.meaning:
The Woman in Lotus Position emoji is a ZWJ sequence combining 🧘 Person in Lotus Position, ‍ Zero Width Joiner and ♀️ Female Sign.
These display as a single emoji on supported platforms.

840.name: Circus Tent
840.meaning: A circular ‘big top’ circus tent, with a triangle flag on top.

841.name: Skateboard
841.meaning: A skateboard emoji, shown on some platforms from the top and others showing the under-side of the board.

842.name: Roller Skate
842.meaning: A single vibrantly colored roller skate. Colors and styles vary across platform.

843.name: Canoe
843.meaning:
Canoe was approved as part of Unicode 9.0 in 2016
and added to Emoji 3.0 in 2016.

844.name: Reminder Ribbon
844.meaning: An awareness ribbon, worn to show support of a cause or group.

845.name: Admission Tickets
845.meaning: A ticket or tickets to an event that may say "Admit One" on the front. Shown in pink or yellow on most platforms.

846.name: Ticket
846.meaning: A paper ticket, which may be for a theatre show, sporting event, or other ticketed performance. Shown in blue, yellow or grey on most platforms.

847.name: Military Medal
847.meaning: A ribbon and medallion generally awarded to a person in the military for heroic acts.

848.name: Trophy
848.meaning: A trophy given as an recognition of achievement, usually in sports. The trophy emoji is a gold cup, with a engraving on the bottom detailing the award.

849.name: Sports Medal
849.meaning: A gold medal, given to a person who has won a sporting event, such as a race. Not to be confused with the military medal emoji.

850.name: 1st Place Medal
850.meaning:
1st Place Medal was approved as part of Unicode 9.0 in 2016
under the name “First Place Medal”
and added to Emoji 3.0 in 2016.

851.name: 2nd Place Medal
851.meaning:
2nd Place Medal was approved as part of Unicode 9.0 in 2016
under the name “Second Place Medal”
and added to Emoji 3.0 in 2016.

852.name: 3rd Place Medal
852.meaning:
3rd Place Medal was approved as part of Unicode 9.0 in 2016
under the name “Third Place Medal”
and added to Emoji 3.0 in 2016.

853.name: Soccer Ball
853.meaning: A round, black and white ball used in the game of soccer, which is known as football in much of the world. See also: emojis for the World Cup.

854.name: Baseball
854.meaning: A white baseball, with regulation red stitching. Used in the game of the same name, baseball.

855.name: Softball
855.meaning: A softball, which is differentiated from a baseball by size (it is larger, though hard to tell in emoji form) and color (yellow, not white).

856.name: Basketball
856.meaning: An orange-colored basketball displayed with a hoop. Many versions of this emoji omit the hoop, and display only the basketball.

857.name: Volleyball
857.meaning: A volleyball emoji, showing the round ball used in the sport. Played as part of the Summer Olympic Games.

858.name: American Football
858.meaning: The oval ball used in the game of American football, known as gridiron in some countries.

859.name: Rugby Football
859.meaning: The oval-shaped ball used in the game of rugby. Varies slightly in shape in the two main versions of the game: rugby union and rugby league.

860.name: Tennis
860.meaning: A tennis racket (racquet) with a tennis ball. Only a ball is shown on Apple, LG, Twitter, Facebook, and Mozilla platforms.

861.name: Flying Disc
861.meaning: A flying disc, more commonly known as a frisbee. Used in the sport of Ultimate or disc golf.

862.name: Bowling
862.meaning: Ten-pin bowling emoji, showing a bowling ball and pins.

863.name: Cricket Game
863.meaning: A cricket bat, with a cricket ball also shown. May be displayed with a wicket present.

864.name: Field Hockey
864.meaning: A hockey stick and ball, used in the sport of field hockey. Not to be confused with the ice hockey stick and puck.

865.name: Ice Hockey
865.meaning: A hockey stick and puck, used in the sport of ice hockey. Not to be confused with the field hockey stick and ball.

866.name: Lacrosse
866.meaning:
Lacrosse was approved as part of Unicode 11.0 in 2018
under the name “Lacrosse Stick and Ball”
and added to Emoji 11.0 in 2018.

867.name: Ping Pong
867.meaning: A paddle and ping pong ball used in the sport of table tennis.

868.name: Badminton
868.meaning:
Badminton was approved as part of Unicode 8.0 in 2015
under the name “Badminton Racquet and Shuttlecock”
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

869.name: Boxing Glove
869.meaning: A padded boxing glove, used in the sport of boxing. Usually red.

870.name: Martial Arts Uniform
870.meaning: A white uniform used in marital arts such as judo or karate. Held together using a material belt. Known as keikogi in Japanese.

871.name: Goal Net
871.meaning:
Goal Net was approved as part of Unicode 9.0 in 2016
and added to Emoji 3.0 in 2016.

872.name: Flag in Hole
872.meaning: A red, triangular flag shown sitting in the hole of a golf course green. Some versions of this emoji also include golf balls.

873.name: Ice Skate
873.meaning: A single ice skate used for ice skating. Shown in white and facing right on most platforms.

874.name: Fishing Pole
874.meaning: A fishing rod (pole) with a fish caught on the end.

875.name: Running Shirt
875.meaning: A singlet or running shirt. Shown with a sash.

876.name: Skis
876.meaning: A pair of skis which are shown on some platforms alongside ski poles and/or ski boots. The color and design of the skis varies by platform, with some versions also showing the skis moving at speed.

877.name: Sled
877.meaning: A sled, otherwise known as a toboggan or sledge.

878.name: Curling Stone
878.meaning:
Curling Stone was approved as part of Unicode 10.0 in 2017
and added to Emoji 5.0 in 2017.

879.name: Direct Hit
879.meaning: A dart board with dart hitting the center / bullseye region.

880.name: Pool 8 Ball
880.meaning: The game of billiards, of which pool is a common version. This emoji displays the black 8 ball on most platforms, which looks similar to the Magic 8-Ball toy.

881.name: Video Game
881.meaning: A video game emoji, shown on major platforms as a console gamepad with D-pad, joysticks, and buttons.

882.name: Slot Machine
882.meaning: A gambling machine generally found in casinos. Shows three wheels with a lever to the side. Most platforms display three 7 digits on this emoji.

883.name: Game Die
883.meaning: A six-sided die, used in a range of board and turn-based games. Commonly called dice which refers to the plural of die.

884.name: Puzzle Piece
884.meaning:
Puzzle Piece was approved as part of Unicode 11.0 in 2018
under the name “Jigsaw Puzzle Piece”
and added to Emoji 11.0 in 2018.

885.name: Chess Pawn
885.meaning:
Chess Pawn was approved as part of Unicode 1.1 in 1993
under the name “Black Chess Pawn”
and added to Emoji 11.0 in 2018.

886.name: Performing Arts
886.meaning: Two masks often used on maps to indicate a theatre, these originate in Greek Theatre as masks of tragedy and comedy.

887.name: Artist Palette
887.meaning: A palette used by an artist when painting, to store and mix paint colors.

888.name: Thread
888.meaning: A spool of thread, as used for sewing. Thread color varies across platforms, though often depicted in red or blue and on a wooden spool. Sometimes shown with an end unraveling.

889.name: Yarn
889.meaning: A ball of yarn, as used to knit a scarf. Color varies across platforms, but often depicted in green, blue, or magenta and shown with an end unraveling. Sometimes depicted with a pair of knitting needles stuck in the ball.

890.name: Musical Score
890.meaning: A staff (or stave) showing a treble clef and five horizontal lines.

891.name: Microphone
891.meaning: A microphone, used to amplify a person’s voice when speaking or singing. Shown with music notes on most platforms, implying it to be used for a singer / singing.

892.name: Headphone
892.meaning: Headphones, used to listen to music or other forms audio, such as podcasts. Most platforms display this emoji with large over-ear headphones in shades of black, blue, and gray.

893.name: Saxophone
893.meaning:
Saxophone was approved as part of Unicode 6.0 in 2010
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

894.name: Accordion
894.meaning:
Accordion was approved as part of Unicode 13.0 in 2020
and added to Emoji 13.0 in 2020.

895.name: Guitar
895.meaning: A guitar, which most platforms display as a red electric guitar.

896.name: Musical Keyboard
896.meaning: A small section of a music keyboard, which differs from a computer keyboard.

897.name: Trumpet
897.meaning: A trumpet, a brass instrument played in jazz bands.

898.name: Violin
898.meaning: A violin emoji. Sometimes used in the context of the world’s smallest violin.

899.name: Drum
899.meaning: A drum shown with drumsticks. A percussion instrument which is likely to be displayed as a snare drum.music, instrument,

900.name: Long Drum
900.meaning:
Long Drum was approved as part of Unicode 13.0 in 2020
and added to Emoji 13.0 in 2020.

901.name: Clapper Board
901.meaning: A board which contains the scene name, number, and film. A person ‘claps’ the board shut at the top while saying “Action” or “Cut” to indicate the start and stop of a scene that is being filmed.

902.name: Bow and Arrow
902.meaning: A bow and arrow used in the sport of archery. May also be used by cupid.

903.name: Person Rowing Boat
903.meaning: A small rowboat suitable for a small number of people. Couples or families sometimes hire these as an activity on calm waters.

904.name: Map of Japan
904.meaning: Shows a map of the country of Japan, which is the only country to have its own emoji map. Other countries can be found on the various globe emojis, or the world map emoji.

905.name: Snow-Capped Mountain
905.meaning: A mountain with snow resting at higher altitudes. Similar in appearance to the Mount Fuji emoji.

906.name: Mountain
906.meaning: A mountain shown with two peaks and blue sky. Similar to the snow capped mountain emoji.

907.name: Volcano
907.meaning: A volcano, erupting with smoke and lava.

908.name: Mount Fuji
908.meaning: Mount Fuji (called Fuji-san in Japan) is the largest mountain in Japan. Often seen with snow on the peak in colder months of the year.

909.name: Camping
909.meaning: A campsite featuring a tent and a tree, and perhaps a campfire. Similar to the tent emoji.

910.name: Beach with Umbrella
910.meaning: A beach showing sand, and an umbrella for protection from the sun.

911.name: Desert
911.meaning:
Desert was approved as part of Unicode 7.0 in 2014
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

912.name: Desert Island
912.meaning:
Desert Island was approved as part of Unicode 7.0 in 2014
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

913.name: National Park
913.meaning: A national park, generally displayed with mountains, a river or stream, and trees.

914.name: Stadium
914.meaning: A large capacity stadium, featuring a large amount of seating for sporting fans, or people attending other shows hosted by the stadium.

915.name: Classical Building
915.meaning: A building shown with columns in a classical style, sometimes used to represent a courthouse, town hall, post office or stock exchange.

916.name: Building Construction
916.meaning: A construction site generally depicted as a tower crane shown lifting steel or other building materials.

917.name: Hut
917.meaning: A round hut with a thatched roof. Used to talk about huts, cottages, yurts, or homes in general.

919.name: Derelict House
919.meaning: A house which is unoccupied, and has become derelict. In a state of disrepair.

920.name: House
920.meaning: A house, otherwise known as a home when someone is living in it. Suitable for a couple or larger family, other perhaps housemates.

921.name: House with Garden
921.meaning: A suburban-looking house, with a tree, flower, or shrubs around it in the garden.

922.name: Office Building
922.meaning: A generic, high-rise office building. Generally found in cities, and most active during business hours.

923.name: Japanese Post Office
923.meaning: A Japanese post office, featuring the テ Japanese postal mark on the front of the building (or showing this mark instead of the building in Microsoft’s artwork).

924.name: Post Office
924.meaning: A European-style post office. A postal horn can be seen on the front, which is commonly found in the logos of European Postal Services.

925.name: Hospital
925.meaning: A place where people are taken to receive medical care. This hospital has a large red cross on the front, often used as a symbol for health care.

926.name: Bank
926.meaning: A retail bank branch, where people can perform money-related tasks. Also a common location to find an ATM.

927.name: Hotel
927.meaning: A hotel building, displayed on most platforms as a building with many windows and a letter H on the front.

928.name: Love Hotel
928.meaning: A love hotel is a hotel that can be hired by the hour instead of as accommodation for the evening.

929.name: Convenience Store
929.meaning: A shop that is generally open for longer hours than a regular supermarket, sometimes 24 hours per day.

930.name: School
930.meaning: A school building with multiple storeys, and a clock on the front. A place that children, or teenagers attend for their education.

931.name: Department Store
931.meaning: A large department store, selling a range of products to the general public. Shown as a large building with a billboard on most platforms, or as a shopping bag on Windows.

932.name: Factory
932.meaning: An industrial factory, with flue-gas stacks releasing exhaust into the air.

933.name: Japanese Castle
933.meaning: A traditional Japanese Castle, usually made from stone and wood.

934.name: Castle
934.meaning: A castle, in a style that can be found in France and other parts of Europe.

935.name: Wedding
935.meaning: An emoji to depict a wedding, displayed by most vendors as a Christian church and love hearts. Some platforms display a cross or bell on the building.

936.name: Tokyo Tower
936.meaning: The Tokyo Tower is the second-tallest building in Japan, located in Minato, Tokyo.

937.name: Statue of Liberty
937.meaning: The Statue of Liberty, often used as a depiction of New York City.

938.name: Church
938.meaning: A church building, generally associated with Christian denominations. In addition quiet prayer, churches hold regular worship services, weddings, baptisms and funerals.

939.name: Mosque
939.meaning: A mosque building, a place of worship for followers of Islam. Shown with a domed roof and a minaret.

940.name: Hindu Temple
940.meaning: A Hindu temple or mandir; a place of worship for followers of Hinduism. Depicted on most platforms as a red, orange, or golden building with a tall spire.

941.name: Synagogue
941.meaning: A synague; a place of worship for followers of Judaism. Displayed with a Star of David on the front.

942.name: Shinto Shrine
942.meaning: A shrine used for the Japanese Shinto religion. This emoji generally displays the torii, which is the gate to the Shinto Shrine. The torii is generally a red colored structure, with a curved roof section above two posts.

943.name: Kaaba
943.meaning: A cube-shaped building located at the centre of the Al-Masjid al-Haram Mosque in Mecca.

944.name: Fountain
944.meaning: A water fountain, found in a park or other public space. Used for decorative purposes. A variety of styles of fountain are shown across different platforms.

945.name: Tent
945.meaning: A tent, used for protection from wind and rain when camping. Often shown at night time, under stars.

946.name: Foggy
946.meaning: Foggy weather displayed as fog covering a bridge or cityscape, depending on the platform. For platforms that show a bridge, the red Golden Gate Bridge is generally displayed.

947.name: Night with Stars
947.meaning: A night sky with stars, depicted on major platforms as a cityscape at night.

948.name: Cityscape
948.meaning:
Cityscape was approved as part of Unicode 7.0 in 2014
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

949.name: Sunrise Over Mountains
949.meaning: The sun rising over a mountain range, early in the morning.

950.name: Sunrise
950.meaning: A sun rising, early in the morning. Can be difficult to distinguish from a sunset in some versions of this artwork.

951.name: Cityscape at Dusk
951.meaning: A view of city buildings as the last light disappears from the sky. An orange (or blue) glow lingers, before the stars of the night sky become visible.

952.name: Sunset
952.meaning: A beautiful view, featuring an orange sky, with the sun setting over the buildings of a city skyline.

953.name: Bridge at Night
953.meaning: A lit-up bridge, shown at night.

954.name: Carousel Horse
954.meaning: A wooden painted horse, found on the carousel at a carnival. Faces to the left-of screen.

955.name: Ferris Wheel
955.meaning: A large rotating wheel, often found at a carnival or fair.

956.name: Roller Coaster
956.meaning: A roller coaster in a theme park going down a dip in the ride. Three carriages can be seen with two people in each red carriage.

957.name: Locomotive
957.meaning: A steam train, powered by coal or wood. An early type of locomotive, now mostly replaced by electric or diesel trains.

958.name: Railway Car
958.meaning: A railway (railroad) car (carriage) that is generally pulled along a railway line by a locomotive. Shown with a pantograph above the carriage on many platforms which makes it look more like a tram car.

959.name: High-Speed Train
959.meaning: A high speed train, designed to cover long distances at high speed.

960.name: Bullet Train
960.meaning: A high speed train, designed to cover long distances at high speed. Also features a streamlined bullet nose, often used in reference to the Shinkansen in Japan.

961.name: Train
961.meaning: A train, of no specified type. Due to the presence of a steam train and fast train emoji, this is likely to be a regular electrified or diesel passenger train.

962.name: Metro
962.meaning: A metro: frequent underground train found in built-up areas with high populations.

963.name: Light Rail
963.meaning: A form of public transport similar to a tram, but running on a track or network separated from cars and other types of traffic.

964.name: Station
964.meaning: A station, presumed to be a train station. Displays a train alongside a platform, where passengers can board.

965.name: Tram
965.meaning: A form of public transport on rails, usually found on streets in cities or other urban areas. For short or medium-length journeys.

966.name: Monorail
966.meaning: Similar to a train, but running on a single track. Monorails are often found at theme parks, or other tourist destinations.

967.name: Mountain Railway
967.meaning: A train and railway in the mountains. Displayed as a funicular in Microsoft’s artwork, or a regular train on other platforms.

968.name: Tram Car
968.meaning: A form of public transport on rails, usually found on streets in cities or other urban areas. For short or medium-length journeys.

969.name: Bus
969.meaning: A bus used for public transport in cities and towns. Could also be used as a school bus.

970.name: Oncoming Bus
970.meaning: The front of a bus, showing the windscreen, as well as wing mirrors in some versions of this emoji.

971.name: Trolleybus
971.meaning: A type of bus that uses overhead electrical wires for power. Appears similar to a cross between a bus and a tram car.

972.name: Minibus
972.meaning: A small bus or minivan designed to carry fewer people than a full-sized bus. Displayed in white on most platforms (green on Facebook).

973.name: Ambulance
973.meaning: An ambulance, used to transport patients between their home and the hospital.

974.name: Fire Engine
974.meaning: A red fire truck, an essential part of emergency services along with a police car or ambulance.

975.name: Police Car
975.meaning: A police car, shown with an emergency light on the top.

976.name: Oncoming Police Car
976.meaning: A police car, shown with an emergency light on the top.

977.name: Taxi
977.meaning: A yellow taxicab, iconically seen in New York City. Shown from the side, as opposed to the oncoming taxi emoji.

978.name: Oncoming Taxi
978.meaning: A yellow taxicab, iconically seen in New York City. Shown from the front, as opposed to the taxi emoji which displays the side of the vehicle.

979.name: Automobile
979.meaning: A car shown from the side, facing right-to-left. Appears as a red car on most platforms (which goes faster), except on Android where this displays as a silver car (previously blue).

980.name: Oncoming Automobile
980.meaning: A car being shown from the front. The windscreen and hood (bonnet in British English) of the car can be seen facing forward.

981.name: Sport Utility Vehicle
981.meaning: A blue or green Sport Utility Vehicle or station wagon, often with a spare tire on the back. Commonly used as a generic blue or green car.

982.name: Pickup Truck
982.meaning: A red or turquoise pickup truck. Used to talk about trucks or modes of transportation in general.

983.name: Delivery Truck
983.meaning:
Delivery Truck was approved as part of Unicode 6.0 in 2010
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

984.name: Articulated Lorry
984.meaning:
Articulated Lorry was approved as part of Unicode 6.0 in 2010
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

985.name: Tractor
985.meaning: A tractor, may be used by a farmer or other occupation on the land.

986.name: Racing Car
986.meaning: A racing car which appears as a formula one vehicle or rally car on most platforms. Generally displayed in red.

987.name: Motorcycle
987.meaning: A motorcycle, otherwise known as a motorbike used for sport/racing purposes. For a transport-based motorcycle, use a motor scooter.

988.name: Motor Scooter
988.meaning: A motor scooter, which may be displayed as any type of motorbike with or without a step-through frame. Distinct from the racing motorcycle, which is used for sport, not transport.

989.name: Auto Rickshaw
989.meaning: An auto rickshaw, often referred to as a tuk tuk. This motorized version of a cycle rickshaw is used for transport in many regions of the world. Generally this emoji has three wheels and open sides without doors.

990.name: Bicycle
990.meaning: A bicycle, sometimes called a push bike, used for transport or sport.

991.name: Kick Scooter
991.meaning: A non-motorized scooter, with two wheels and handles.

992.name: Bus Stop
992.meaning: A sign indicating the location of a bus stop by the side of a road.

993.name: Motorway
993.meaning: A wide road shown from a first person perspective. Apple's artwork displays a road sign to Curpertino.

994.name: Railway Track
994.meaning:
Railway Track was approved as part of Unicode 7.0 in 2014
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

995.name: Fuel Pump
995.meaning: A fuel pump, used to fill up a vehicle with gas / petrol.

996.name: Police Car Light
996.meaning: A revolving red light seen on top of a police car. Often used in emergency circumstances in addition to a siren making a loud warning sound.

997.name: Horizontal Traffic Light
997.meaning: A set of red, orange (amber) and green traffic lights, used at intersections. Less common than the vertical traffic light.

998.name: Vertical Traffic Light
998.meaning: A set of red, orange (amber) and green traffic lights, used at intersections. More common than the horizontal traffic light.

999.name: Construction
999.meaning: A sign used to indicate roadwork or construction. Generally shown as yellow and black diagonal stripes, and often used to physically block access to a road or area. May be used to imply a website or project in progress or under construction.

1000.name: Anchor
1000.meaning: A metal device, dropped out of a boat to prevent it drifting away from the current location.

1001.name: Sailboat
1001.meaning: A sailboat, otherwise known as a sailing boat or yacht.  Uses wind as the source of propulsion to move around a body of water.

1002.name: Speedboat
1002.meaning: A motorized speedboat used for recreation on lakes, or other bodies of water.

1003.name: Passenger Ship
1003.meaning:
Passenger Ship was approved as part of Unicode 7.0 in 2014
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

1004.name: Ferry
1004.meaning:
Ferry was approved as part of Unicode 5.2 in 2009
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

1005.name: Motor Boat
1005.meaning:
Motor Boat was approved as part of Unicode 7.0 in 2014
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

1006.name: Ship
1006.meaning: A large ship, used for transport of people or cargo across the ocean. May be a cruise ship, commonly found around tropical locations.

1007.name: Airplane
1007.meaning: Used either as a literal airplane, to represent an overseas vacation, or sometimes as a proxy for airplane mode on a phone or tablet.

1008.name: Small Airplane
1008.meaning: A light aircraft which is shown with propellers on some platforms.

1009.name: Airplane Departure
1009.meaning: A plane taking off from a runway. Generally displayed left-right, with the front of the plane elevated.

1010.name: Airplane Arrival
1010.meaning: A plane approaching a runway for landing. Generally displayed left-right, with the front of the plane facing toward the ground in a position that may result in a crash if attempted in the real world.

1011.name: Parachute
1011.meaning: An open parachute floating through the air with a human steering. Most platforms feature a ram-air design. Colors vary across platforms.

1012.name: Seat
1012.meaning: A seat, which could refer to any form of place to sit, with the distinction that a seat is generally fixed, and is not a chair which can be moved.

1013.name: Helicopter
1013.meaning: A helicopter, which can hover in the air. Often seen in emergency circumstances such as transporting patients to a hospital, or for police or fire-fighting activity.

1014.name: Suspension Railway
1014.meaning: Similar to a monorail, a suspension railway is elevated, but the vehicle is suspended under the track.

1015.name: Mountain Cableway
1015.meaning:
Mountain Cableway was approved as part of Unicode 6.0 in 2010
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

1016.name: Aerial Tramway
1016.meaning: An Aerial Tramway, most commonly seen at ski resorts, for transport between locations on a mountain. Can also be used as a tourist attraction, or as a form of public transport.

1017.name: Satellite
1017.meaning: A satellite which orbits the earth, and is generally used for communications, weather, and GPS.

1018.name: Rocket
1018.meaning: A rocket being propelled into space. Sometimes used to indicate a fast increase, for instance when referring to stocks going to the moon 🚀 (rising quickly in price).

1019.name: Flying Saucer
1019.meaning: A flying saucer, sometimes referred to as an Unidentified Flying Object (UFO). Shown on some platforms with an alien at the controls and/or a beam of light emitting from the base.

1020.name: Ringed Planet
1020.meaning: A ringed planet that appears with various number of rings, tilt angles, and colors across platforms. This vaguely Saturn-like orb was proposed as a stand-alone planet emoji to represent all planets.

1021.name: Shooting Star
1021.meaning: A stylized representation of a shooting star, a small, fast meteor that burns up in the atmosphere. Generally depicted as a gold, five-point star trailing yellow motion lines against a night sky, as if moving down to the left.

1022.name: Milky Way
1022.meaning: The Milky Way – a galaxy of billions of stars that includes our own solar system and planet earth.

1023.name: Umbrella on Ground
1023.meaning: A large, open umbrella, as provides shade at a beach or patio. Generally depicted as a striped umbrella inserted into a patch of sand and tilted to the right.

1024.name: Fireworks
1024.meaning: Firework emoji, showing a explosion of colored light in the night sky, used for any number of celebrations such as New Year's Eve.

1025.name: Sparkler
1025.meaning: A  sparkler: a form of hand-held firework often used at parties and celebrations. The sparkler is lit at one end, and held at the other.

1026.name: Moon Viewing Ceremony
1026.meaning: Moon Viewing Ceremonies (called Tsukimi in Japan) are held each year in autumn to celebrate the full moon and waxing moon in Japan.

1027.name: Yen Banknote
1027.meaning: A banded stack of yen banknotes, the paper currency of Japan. Color and detail vary across platforms, but usually shown in green, yellow, or pink with the yen symbol, ¥. Commonly used for various content concerning money and wealth, not restricted to Japan.

1028.name: Dollar Banknote
1028.meaning: Cash money! A banded stack of U.S. dollar banknotes, the paper currency of the United States of America. Green hue and detail vary across platforms, but shown with the dollar sign, $. Commonly used for various content concerning wealth and money, not restricted to the U.S.

1029.name: Euro Banknote
1029.meaning: A banded stack of euro banknotes, the paper currency of the European Union (EU). Color and detail vary across platforms, but shown with the euro sign, €. Commonly used for various content concerning wealth and money, not restricted to the EU.

1030.name: Pound Banknote
1030.meaning: Quids in! A banded stack of pound banknotes, the paper currency of the United Kingdom (England, Wales, Northern Ireland, and Scotland). Color and detail vary across platforms, but widely depicted as purple £20 notes with the pound sign, £.

1031.name: Moai
1031.meaning: A moai, one of the famed, giant stone statues of human figures on Easter Island. Depicted as a gray stone carving of a stylized human head with a prominent brow and nose, most often facing left.

1032.name: Passport Control
1032.meaning: A person checking passports at an international border.

1033.name: Customs
1033.meaning: A customs officer inspecting luggage. May be shown on signage at airports or other border crossings.

1034.name: Baggage Claim
1034.meaning:
Baggage Claim was approved as part of Unicode 6.0 in 2010
and added to Emoji 1.0 in 2015.

1035.name: Left Luggage
1035.meaning: An icon representing a place to leave luggage. Most commonly found at Japanese train stations to signify coin lockers where bags can be stored for a daily fee.

1036.name: Love Letter
1036.meaning: The back of an envelope, generally shown in white and sealed with a red heart. Represents a love letter or note, valentine, or affectionate greeting card. Commonly used to convey various feelings or messages of love and happiness.

1037.name: Hole
1037.meaning: A round, black, cartoon-styled hole, as a manhole or a hole (cup) in golf. May be used to represent various types of literal or figurative holes, e.g., black holes, rabbit holes.

1038.name: Bomb
1038.meaning: A cartoon-styled bomb, depicted as a black ball with a burning fuse.

1039.name: Person Taking Bath
1039.meaning: A gender-unspecified person taking a soothing bath in a white tub with a shower head. Commonly used for various content concerning bathing, washing, cleaning, and bathrooms more generally. May also represent relaxation and self-care.

1040.name: Person in Bed
1040.meaning: A bed with a gender-unspecified person sleeping in it, as at a house, hotel, hostel, or other sleeping accommodation. Used especially for various content concerning sleeping as well as beds, furniture, housing, relaxing, and other bedroom activities.

1041.name: Kitchen Knife
1041.meaning: A knife with a long steel blade, as a chef uses to slice meat or vegetables. Depicted with a black or brown handle and positioned at a 45° angle, often with its point at the lower right.

1042.name: Amphora
1042.meaning: A tall, ceramic jar with two handles and a narrow neck and foot. Represents an amphora, as used by ancient Greeks and Romans to hold water and wine.

1043.name: World Map
1043.meaning: A rectangular map of the world. Generally depicted as a paper map creased at its folds, Earth’s surface shown in green on blue ocean.

1044.name: Compass
1044.meaning: A magnetic compass, as used for navigation. Generally depicted in a silver or gold case with a compass rose and a red-tipped needle. Commonly used for various content concerning traveling and exploring as well as metaphorical compasses (e.g., moral compass).

1045.name: Brick
1045.meaning: A red brick or bricks. Depicted in a loose stack, a single object with holes, or as built into wall, as of a house, school, or other structure.

1046.name: Barber Pole
1046.meaning: A pole spiraled with red, white, and blue stripes, as spins out front of a barbershop. Commonly used for various content concerning haircutting and hairstyling.

1047.name: Manual Wheelchair
1047.meaning: A manual wheelchair. Most platforms show a red and black or blue and black wheelchair. Distinct from ♿ Wheelchair Symbol, which is used as signage to indicate accessible facilities. See also 👩‍🦽Woman in Manual Wheelchair or 👨‍🦽Man in Manual Wheelchair.

1048.name: Motorized Wheelchair
1048.meaning: A motorized wheelchair. Most platforms show a red and black or blue and black wheelchair. Distinct from ♿ Wheelchair Symbol which is used as signage to indicate accessible facilities. See also 👩‍🦼Woman in Motorized Wheelchair or 👨‍🦼Man in Motorized Wheelchair.

1049.name: Oil Drum
1049.meaning: A barrel for transporting bulk liquids, such as oil. Generally depicted as a red or blue metal drum with holes or a stopper on its lid. Commonly used for various content concerning petroleum or hazardous waste.

1050.name: Bellhop Bell
1050.meaning: Ding! A call bell, as pressed at a front desk or reception to alert staff for service, such as from a concierge or bellhop (porter) to carry luggage at a hotel. Generally depicted as a golden bell on a wooden stand.

1051.name: Luggage
1051.meaning: A suitcase or bag, as used for traveling. Most platforms depict gray or blue rolling luggage with an extended handle. Commonly used for various content concerning traveling or taking trips, whether for business or leisure.

1052.name: Hourglass Done
1052.meaning: A classic hourglass, all of its sand having flowed into the bottom bulb. Indicates time has passed. Color varies across platforms.

1053.name: Hourglass Not Done
1053.meaning: A classic hourglass, its sand still flowing from the top to bottom bulb. Indicates time is still passing—but life is short. Color varies across platforms.

1054.name: Watch
1054.meaning: A wristwatch, as used for telling time. Appearance varies across platforms, but widely depicted as an analog timepiece with a white face and brown or black straps.

1055.name: Alarm Clock
1055.meaning: A timepiece set in advance to startle a person awake at the designated time with its two bells. That is, before hitting snooze. Appearance varies across platforms, but depicted as a classic, wind-up, bedside alarm clock, often red in color.

1056.name: Stopwatch
1056.meaning: An analog, handheld timepiece used to measure elapsed time, as for athletic sprints. Appearance varies across platforms, but depicted with two or more control buttons on its top.

1057.name: Timer Clock
1057.meaning: Time’s up! A timer set to count down and sound an alarm after a designated amount of time, as used in the kitchen. Appearance varies by platform. Commonly used for various content concerning time, including countdowns and deadlines.

1058.name: Mantelpiece Clock
1058.meaning: An antique-styled mantel clock with a flat base and rounded case, as made of wood and brass and placed above a fireplace.

1059.name: Thermometer
1059.meaning: A liquid-in-glass thermometer, as used to measure temperature. Depicted at various angles with a red liquid risen from the bulb to various levels on the scale. Commonly used for content concerning high temperatures, including warm weather, illness (having a fever), and various slang senses of hot.

1060.name: Umbrella on Ground
1060.meaning: A large, open umbrella, as provides shade at a beach or patio. Generally depicted as a striped umbrella inserted into a patch of sand and tilted to the right.

1061.name: Firecracker
1061.meaning: A firecracker, as lit on Chinese New Year, New Year's Eve, or Independence Day. Depicted as a red tube with a burning fuse, sometimes lined with gold rings at its top and base.

1062.name: Balloon
1062.meaning: A balloon on a string, as decorates a birthday party. Generally depicted in red, though WhatsApp’s is pink and Google’s orangish-red.

1063.name: Party Popper
1063.meaning: A party popper, as explodes in a shower of confetti and streamers at a celebration. Generally depicted as a gold party hat, striped on some platforms, at a 45° angle, with multicolored confetti and streamers coming from its opening at the upper right. Twitter’s cone is red.

1064.name: Confetti Ball
1064.meaning: A golden ball, split in two halves in a shower of multicolored confetti and streamers.

1065.name: Japanese Dolls
1065.meaning: Ornamental Japanese Emperor and Empress dolls, as displayed in celebration of Hinamatsuri on March 3 in Japan (Girls’ or Dolls’ Day).

1066.name: Carp Streamer
1066.meaning: Japanese koinobori, decorative, carp-shaped windsocks flown in celebration of Children’s Day on May 5 in Japan. Generally depicted as a blue and red stylized carp fish on a golden pole.

1067.name: Wind Chime
1067.meaning: A Japanese wind chime. Depicted as a glass bell with a strip of paper suspended from its clapper, often decorated with cherry blossom-like flowers.

1068.name: Red Envelope
1068.meaning: A red envelope, as gifted with money on Chinese New Year or on other joyous occasions, such as weddings, in Chinese and some other Asian cultures around the world.

1069.name: Ribbon
1069.meaning: A pink or red ribbon, as tied into a bow on a gift or woman's hat.

1070.name: Wrapped Gift
1070.meaning: A present or gift in a box tied with a bow, as given on a birthday or Christmas. Box and ribbon color vary across platforms, but commonly depicted as a gold box with a lid wrapped with a red ribbon.

1071.name: Diving Mask
1071.meaning: A diving mask with a snorkel, used for scuba diving or other underwater activities. Colors vary across platforms.

1072.name: Yo-Yo
1072.meaning: A round yo-yo with its string coming out. It appears in various colors and designs across platforms.

1073.name: Kite
1073.meaning: A diamond-shaped kite with a tail. This emoji appears in various colors across platforms.

1074.name: Crystal Ball
1074.meaning: A crystal ball, as a fortune teller or clairvoyant gazes into to tell the future. Depicted as a sparkling, purple or blue crystal orb resting on a stand.

1075.name: Magic Wand
1075.meaning: A wand with sparkles (✨magic✨) coming out of its end. Most platforms show a classic magician-style magic wand that's black with white tips. WhatsApp shows a golden magic wand tipped with a star, similar to the wand that Glenda the Good Witch uses in the 1939 film The Wizard of Oz.

1076.name: Nazar Amulet
1076.meaning: A nazar, an eye-shaped amulet believed to protect against the evil eye, especially in Turkish culture. Depicted as a rich blue, circular bead with a black dot in the center ringed with white and light blue, resembling an eye.

1077.name: Joystick
1077.meaning: A joystick, as used in playing classic arcade, computer, or video games. Generally depicted with a black base, red-knobbed control stick, and one or more red buttons.

1078.name: Teddy Bear
1078.meaning: A classic teddy bear, as snuggled by a child when going to sleep.

1079.name: Piñata
1079.meaning: A colorful decorated container that comes in many shapes, a piñata is filled with candy or toys. Hit to break open for celebrations such as Cinco de Mayo, this is generally associated with Mexico.

1080.name: Nesting Dolls
1080.meaning:
Nesting Dolls was approved as part of Unicode 13.0 in 2020
and added to Emoji 13.0 in 2020.

1081.name: Framed Picture
1081.meaning: A framed picture of a painting or photograph, as displayed in a gallery or on a household wall. Vendors feature various scenes, though generally a lush, sunny landscape of hills and mountains, in a gold frame.

1082.name: Thread
1082.meaning: A spool of thread, as used for sewing. Thread color varies across platforms, though often depicted in red or blue and on a wooden spool. Sometimes shown with an end unraveling.

1083.name: Sewing Needle
1083.meaning:
Sewing Needle was approved as part of Unicode 13.0 in 2020
and added to Emoji 13.0 in 2020.

1084.name: Yarn
1084.meaning: A ball of yarn, as used to knit a scarf. Color varies across platforms, but often depicted in green, blue, or magenta and shown with an end unraveling. Sometimes depicted with a pair of knitting needles stuck in the ball.

1085.name: Knot
1085.meaning:
Knot was approved as part of Unicode 13.0 in 2020
and added to Emoji 13.0 in 2020.

1086.name: Shopping Bags
1086.meaning: Two colorful shopping bags, as contain consumer items bought at a department store. Depicted as gift bags in various bright colors, patterns, sizes, and positions across platforms. Apple's design, for instance, features a pink bag with light-pink dots in front of a gold bag with yellow stripes.

1087.name: Prayer Beads
1087.meaning: A string of beads, as used in prayer or meditation in many religious traditions. Generally depicted as red, wooden beads with a gold, decorative center bead and tassel.

1088.name: Gem Stone
1088.meaning: A jewel or gem, as set into a ring. Depicted in the shape of a classic diamond but in the bright blue color of an aquamarine.

1089.name: Postal Horn
1089.meaning: A postal horn (post horn). Depicted as a coiled, valveless, brass horn, like a bugle or trumpet, with two red tassels. Sometimes used to mark announcements as well as for various content concerning brass instruments, music, or mail.

1090.name: Studio Microphone
1090.meaning: A microphone, as used for radio broadcasting or studio recording. Most platforms depict a vintage, silver microphone, like the Shure Unidyne 55.

1091.name: Level Slider
1091.meaning: A level slider, as adjusts volume on a mixing console. Most platforms depict a silver and black channel fader with scale markings, set to various levels. Apple and Google's go up to eleven.

1092.name: Control Knobs
